Major - General John Clitherow ( 13 December 1782 -- 14 October 1852 ) was an army officer , politician and was briefly Lieutenant Governor of Canada West and Canada East ( 1841 ) .
Giovanni Pietro Possenti ( 1618 - -1659 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , active mainly as a battle painter .
Herman Berlinski ( 18 August 1910 -- 27 September 2001 ) was a German - born American composer , organist , pianist , musicologist and choir conductor .
Lotika Zellermeier ( Serbian : Лотика Цилермајер/Lotika Cilermajer ) ( 1860 , Kraków , Poland -- 1938 , Višegrad , Yugoslavia ) was the inspiration for the main character from the 1961 Nobel Prize winner Ivo Andrić 's novel The Bridge on the Drina .
Rinaldo Priora ( Turin , October 12 , 1864 -- 1942 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of still lifes and landscapes .
Mihaela Ursuleasa ( 27 September 1978 -- 2 August 2012 ) was a Romanian concert pianist .
Sadhana Shivdasani ( 2 September 1941 -- 25 December 2015 ) , better known mononymously as Sadhana , was an Indian actress who was one of the top actresses in the 1960s and the early-1970s , a period regarded as Bollywood 's `` golden era '' .
Blessed Giovanna Francesca Michelotti ( 29 August 1843 -- 1 February 1888 ) , born Anna Michelotti , was an Italian Roman Catholic nun .
Avraham - Haim Shag ( Hebrew : אברהם - חיים שאג‎ , born Avraham - Haim Tzvebner on 17 July 1883 , died 6 December 1958 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Assembly of Representatives and the Knesset .
John Lovelace , 2nd Baron Lovelace ( February 1616 -- 25 November 1670 was a British peer and Royal servant .
Leonard Blunt ( 21 March 1929 -- July 2005 ) was a cricketer who played first - class cricket for Worcestershire and the Europeans in the 1940s .
Frederick Mortimer Clapp ( July 26 , 1879 -- 1969 ) was the first Director of the Frick Collection in Manhattan , New York , as well as a poet , and art historian .
Riccardo Pazzaglia ( 12 September 1926 -- 4 October 2006 ) was an Italian actor , film director , screenwriter , songwriter ( for Domenico Modugno ) , TV and radio personality .
Jack McDonough ( 26 July 1879 -- 23 February 1955 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Giovanni Battista Falcieri ( known as `` Tita '' ) ( 1798 - -1874 ) was the personal servant of Lord Byron and was present at his death in Missolonghi in 1824 .
Neil Tucker ( 9 May 1915 -- 6 October 1981 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Francisco de las Carreras ( 1809 - -1870 ) was an Argentine lawyer , judge and politician .
Robert Byron Miller ( 19 April 1825 -- 5 October 1902 ) was a lawyer and politician in colonial Tasmania .
Edmund Sedding ( 20 June 1836 - -1868 ) was an English architect and musician .
John Shirreff ( 1759 - -1818 ) was a Scottish agricultural writer .
Felton Snow ( October 23 , 1905 -- July 1974 ) was a Negro League professional baseball player who played for the Nashville Elite Giants that later became the Columbus Elite Giants , the Washington Elite Giants , and the Baltimore Elite Giants .
Totila , original name Baduila ( died July 1 , 552 ) was the penultimate King of the Ostrogoths , reigning from 541 to 552 AD .
Bécc mac Airemóin ( died 893 ) or Bécc mac Éiremóin was a Dál Fiatach king of Ulaid , which is now Ulster , Ireland .
Edward Salomons ( 1828 - -1906 ) was an Anglo - Jewish architect based in Manchester , working in the late 19th century .
Thomas F. Byrnes ( June 15 , 1842 -- May 7 , 1910 ) was an Irish - born American police officer , who served as head of the New York City Police Department detective department from 1880 until 1895 , and gained national attention for his exploits .
Khalilullah I ( Halil ) ( 1418 - -1465 ) was 34th ruler of Shirvan and son of Ibrahim I of Shirvan .
Willem van de Velde the Elder ( c. 1611 -- 13 December 1693 ) was a Dutch Golden Age seascape painter .
Béatrix de Cusance ( 27 December 1614 -- 5 June 1663 ) , Baroness of Belvoir , was the second wife of Charles IV , former reigning Duke of Lorraine .
Camillo Gavasetti ( 1596 - 1630 ) was a native of Modena , who flourished about the year 1626 .
Robert Gittler committed suicide in 1978 before the theatrical release of The Buddy Holly Story .
Sang - nu ( 상루 , 尙婁 ) ( died 294 ) was the Prime Minister of Goguryeo during the reign of King Seocheon , and the son of previous Prime Minister Eum - u .
John Jabez Thurston ( 11 October 1888 -- 8 January 1960 ) was an independent member of the Canadian House of Commons .
Thomas Boutflower Bennett ( 1808- 14 September 1894 ) was an early colonist of South Australia , remembered as a schoolmaster at J. L. Young 's Adelaide Educational Institution and at Saint Peter 's College .
Shaul Berezovsky ( sometimes spelt Berezowski ) ( 1908 - 1975 ) was a Polish Jewish composer , pianist , music director .
John Kruse ( 1921 - -2004 ) was an English film and television screenwriter , director and novelist .
Sir Grafton Elliot Smith , FRS FRCP ( 15 August 1871 -- 1 January 1937 ) was an Australian - British anatomist and a proponent of the hyperdiffusionist view of prehistory .
Dai Longbang ( Chinese : 戴龍邦 ) ( 1732?--1801 ) was a Chinese master of the internal martial art of Xinyiquan ( Heart and Intention Boxing ) , the precursor of Xingyiquan ( Form and Intention Boxing ) .
Anjanibai Malpekar ( 22 April 1883 -- 7 August 1974 ) was a noted Indian classical singer , belonging to the Bhendibazaar gharana of Hindustani classical music .
Agnes McLaren ( 4 July 1837 -- 17 April 1913 ) was a respected Scottish doctor who was the first to give medical assistance to women in India who , because of custom , were unable to access medical help from male doctors .
Eifan Saadoun Al Issawi ( died 15 January 2013 ) was an Iraqi politician who was killed in a suicide bombing attack on 15 January 2013 .
Samuel Wix ( 1771 - -1861 ) was an English cleric and controversialist .
Joseph Charles Fowell ( 2 August 1891 - 3 July 1970 ) was a prominent Australian 20th century architect .
Sir William Gammie Ogg ( 1891 - -1979 ) was a British horticultural scientist and Director of Rothamsted Experimental Station
Jean - Joseph Dassy , a French historical and portrait painter , and lithographer , was born at Marseilles on December 27 , 1791 and died in the same city on July 27 , 1865 .
Natalino Otto , stage name of Natale Codognotto ( 24 December 1912 -- 4 October 1969 ) was an Italian singer .
George Lister Sutcliffe ( died September 1915 ) was an English Arts and Crafts architect and author of a number of technical and architectural publications .
Sallie Martin ( November 20 , 1895 -June 18 , 1988 ) was a gospel singer nicknamed `` the mother of gospel music '' for her efforts to popularize the songs of Thomas A. Dorsey and her influence on other artists .
Jamie Kyne ( 1991 -- 5 September 2009 ) was an Irish jockey .
Ali Alatas ( Arabic : علي العطاس‎ ʿAlī al-ʿAṭṭās ; 4 November 1932 -- 11 December 2008 ) was an Indonesian diplomat of Ba ' Alawi sada descent , who served as the country 's foreign minister from 1988 to 1999 .
Richard Conyers ( 1725 - -1786 ) was an English evangelical cleric , and the hymn - book compiler of a precursor to the Olney Hymns .
Raja Bahadur Venkatarama Reddy ( August 1869 - 1953 ) was the first Hindu to be made kotwal of Hyderabad as in the late 19th and early 20th century , during the Islamic rule of the Nizams , the powerful position of kotwal of Hyderabad was held only by Muslims .
Norman Macleod Ferrers D.D. ( 11 August 1829 -- 31 January 1903 ) was a British mathematician and university administrator and editor of a mathematical journal .
Karel Albert Rudolf Bosscha , sometimes known as KAR Bosscha or Ru Bosscha ( The Hague , 15 May 1865 -- Malabar , Indonesia , 26 November 1928 ) was a planter , philanthropist and administrator of the Malabar Plantation in Bandung , Indonesia .
Semen Paliy ( Ukrainian : Семен Палiй , Polish : Semen Palej ) ( c. 1645 -- 1710 ) was a Ukrainian Cossack polkovnyk ( colonel ) .
Halbert L. Dunn , M.D. ( 1896 - -1975 ) was the leading figure in establishing a national vital statistics system in the United States and is known as the `` father of the wellness movement '' .
Jean Danjou ( 15 April 1828 -- 30 April 1863 ) was a decorated captain in the French Foreign Legion .
Qin Jiushao ( Chinese : 秦九韶 ; pinyin : Qín Jiǔsháo ; Wade -- Giles : Ch'in Chiu - shao , ca . 1202 - -1261 ) , courtesy name Daogu ( 道古 ) , was a Chinese mathematician .
Paul Moon James ( 1780 - -1854 ) was a successful English banker , who worked in partnership with Samuel Galton junior in Steelhouse Lane , Birmingham .
Arthur Stayner ( 29 March 1835 -- 4 September 1899 ) was an English horticulturist who emigrated to the United States and became important in the founding of the sugar beet industry in Utah .
H. E. Todd ( 1908 - -1988 ) was a British writer of children 's fiction .
Luiz Heitor Corrêa de Azevedo ( Rio de Janeiro , 13 December 1905 -- Paris , 10 November , 1992 ) was a Brazilian journalist , musicologist and folklorist .
Mary Ellicott Arnold ( April 23 , 1876 - -1968 ) was an American social activist , teacher and writer best known for In the Land of the Grasshopper Song , the memoir she wrote with Mabel Reed ( 1876 - -1963 ) on their experiences as Bureau of Indian Affairs employees , 1908 - -1909 .
Murong Fuyun ( 慕容伏允 ) ( 597 - -635 ) , formal title Busabo Khan ( 步薩鉢可汗 ) , was a ruler of the Xianbei state Tuyuhun .
Charles Fenerty ( January , 1821 -- 10 June 1892 ) , was a Canadian inventor who invented the wood pulp process for papermaking , which was first adapted into the production of newsprint .
Sir Goday Narayana Gajapathi Rao KCIE ( December 1 , 1828 - May 1903 ) was an Indian aristocrat and politician who served as a member of the Madras Legislative Council from 1868 to 1884 .
Sir Lewis McIver , 1st Baronet ( 6 March 1846 -- 9 August 1920 ) was a British Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1885 and 1909 .
Jamaluddin Abro , ( Sindhi : جمال الدين ابڙو‎ - Urdu : جمال الدین ابڑو ‎ ) also known as Jamal Abro ( 2 May 1924 -- 30 June 2004 , Larkana , Pakistan ) was a Sindhi writer .
Captain William Frederick Strickland ( 1 February 1880 -- 29 November 1954 ) was a Conservative Member of Parliament ( MP ) representing Coventry , from 1931 to 1945 .
Josef Swickard ( 26 June 1866 -- 29 February 1940 ) was a German - born veteran stage and screen character actor , who had toured with stock companies in Europe , South Africa , and South America .
Earl L. Warrick ( 1911 - -2002 ) was an industrial chemist at Dow Corning who is noted for his claim to being the inventor of Silly Putty .
John William Muir ( 15 December 1879 -- 11 January 1931 ) was the editor of The Worker who was prosecuted under the Defense of the Realm Act for an article criticising the war .
Malcolm Bruce Smith ( 29 February 1924 -- 27 July 2000 ) was an Australian chemist who studied the egg protein ovalbumin .
Major - General William Farquhar ( /ˈfɑːkər/ FAH - kər ; 26 February 1774 -- 11 May 1839 ) was an employee of the East India Company , and the first Resident of colonial and Commandant British of Singapore .
Guillaume Cousinot de Montreuil ( 1400 - -1484 ) was a French diplomat , magistrate and civil servant .
Nora Dunfee ( 25 December 1915 -- 23 December 1994 ) was an American Broadway and film actress and acting coach .
Cresheld Draper ( 8 November 1646 -- 15 March 1694 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1678 to 1689 .
Sir Chimanlal Harilal Setalvad , KCIE ( 1864 - 10 December 1947 ) was an eminent Indian barrister who practiced in the Bombay High Court in the early 20th century .
César Alfredo Miró Quesada Bahamonde ( 1907 - -1999 ) , more commonly known as César Miró , was a Peruvian writer and composer .
Oliver Samuel Tonks , Ph.D. ( 1874 - -1953 ) was a professor of art at Vassar College .
Brian Brolly ( 21 October 1936 -- 28 October 2006 ) , was an English showbusiness entrepreneur .
Ephraim Peabody ( 22 March 1807 Wilton , New Hampshire - 28 November 1856 Boston , Massachusetts ) was a Unitarian clergyman from the United States .
Henrietta Hill Swope ( October 26 , 1902 - November 24 , 1980 ) was an American astronomer who studied variable stars .
Godfrey Winham ( December 11 , 1934 - -April 26 , 1975 ) was an English - born music theorist and composer of contemporary classical music who moved to the United States .
Peter Dombrovskis ( 2 March 1945 -- 28 March 1996 ) was an Australian photographer , known for his Tasmanian scenes .
Adam Bellenden ( c. 1569 - -1647 ) was a 17th - century Scottish churchman .
Henriette Arendt ( 11 November 1874 -- 22 August 1922 ) was a German writer and policewoman .
Sir Richard Pakenham PC ( 19 May 1797 -- 28 October 1868 ) was a British diplomat .
Lord Ian Basil Gawaine Hamilton - Temple - Blackwood ( 4 November 1870 -- 3 July 1917 ) , known as Lord Basil Temple Blackwood , was a British lawyer , civil servant and book illustrator .
Olavi Hänninen ( 14 December 1920 , Lapinlahti -- 16 June 1992 ) was a Finnish designer and interior architect .
Colonel Sir Henry Simpson Newland CBE DSO ( 24 November 1873 -- 13 November 1969 ) was a distinguished Australian surgeon .
Niels Jacobsen ( 14 September 1865 - 31 January 1935 ) was a Danish architect and politician who worked primarily in Odense .
William Cruden ( 1726 - -1785 ) was a Scottish minister and author .
Mordechai Avida ( 1909 - -1986 ) , born Mordechai Zlotnik , was a radio broadcaster of Kol Israel in its preliminary stages .
Gina Krog ( 20 June 1847 -- 14 April 1916 ) was a Norwegian feminist pioneer , teacher , liberal politician and editor .
Richard Barry Parker ( 18 November 1867 -- 21 February 1947 ) was an English architect and urban planner associated with the Arts and Crafts Movement .
Usmar Ismail ( 20 March 1921 -- 2 January 1971 ) was a prominent Indonesian film director .
Elena de Galantha ( 24 November 1890 -- 5 January 1986 ) considered a pioneer in the field of modern histology and known for the de Galantha technique and the de Galantha stain .
Reza Mahjubi ( Persian : رضا محجوبی‎ ) , ( birth date : 1898 - 14 July 1954 ) was a Persian ( Iranian ) composer and violinist .
Christopher St Lawrence , 2nd Baron Howth ( died 1462 or 1465 ) was an Anglo - Irish nobleman .
Xu Fancheng ( Chinese : 徐梵澄 ) ( 26 October 1909 - 6 March 2000 ) , also known as Hu Hsu in India , was a Chinese scholar and translator .
Edward Budge ( 1800 - -1865 ) was an English theologian , geologist , and general writer .
David Foggie RSA ( 31 December 1878 Dundee -- 2 June 1948 ) , was a Scots painter , son of James and Margaret Foggie .
James Williamson , 1st Baron Ashton ( 31 December 1842 -- 27 May 1930 ) was a British businessman and Liberal Party politician , whose family business in Lancaster produced oilcloth and linoleum which was exported around the world .
Wilfred J. Delaney- O'Dubhshlaine ( c. 1937 South Boston -- August 4 , 1964 Port of Boston ) was a member of the McLaughlin gang who was a friend and associate of Harold Hannon , a contract killer who had murdered boxer Tommy Sullivan in 1957 .
Lisa Daniely ( born Mary Elizabeth Bodington ; 4 June 1929 -- 24 January 2014 ) , was a British film and television actress .
Arun Nehru ( 24 April 1944 -- 25 July 2013 ) was an Indian politician and columnist .
Ebenezer Thomas Davies , known as E. T. Davies ( Pontycymer , Glamorgan 1903 -- 1991 ) was a scholar , schoolmaster and Anglican priest in the Church in Wales .
William Kreiten ( 21 June 1847 , in Gangelt near Aachen -- 6 June 1902 , at Kerkrade ( Kirchrath ) in Limburg ) was a literary critic and poet .
Zhang Dongsun ( 张东荪 ; also transliterated as Chang Tung - sun ) ( 1886 - -1973 ) was a Chinese philosopher , public intellectual and political figure .
Maharani Datar Kaur ( died 1838 ) , the daughter of Sardar Ran Singh Nakai , the third ruler of Nakai Misl of Baherwal , was the second wife of Maharaja Ranjit Singh .
Mike M. Liskany ( died 1971 ) was an American labor leader and politician of the Democratic party .
Charles Debbas ( Arabic : شارل دباس‎ ) ( 16 April 1885 - 1935 ) was an Eastern Orthodox Lebanese political figure .
Mohan Lal Sukhadia ( 31 July 1916 -- 2 February 1982 ) was an Indian politician , who served as the Chief Minister of Rajasthan state for 17 years ( 1954 - -1971 ) .
Gianni Lancia ( 16 November 1924 -- 30 June 2014 ) was an Italian former automobile engineer , industrialist and racing enthusiast , known for running the Lancia carmaker in Torino ( 1949 - -55 ) .
John Longbotham ( died 1801 ) was a canal engineer and pupil of John Smeaton who in 1766 suggested a Leeds and Liverpool Canal and did a survey which was approved by James Brindley .
Ronald William Wycherley ( 17 April 1940 -- 28 January 1983 ) , better known by his stage name Billy Fury , was an English singer from the late 1950s to the mid 1960s , and remained an active songwriter until the 1980s .
Philip Dorn ( 30 September 1901 -- 9 May 1975 ) , born Hein van der Niet and sometimes billed as Frits van Dongen , was a Dutch actor who had a career in Hollywood .
Thomas Henry Ismay ( 7 January 1837 -- 23 November 1899 ) was the founder of the Oceanic Steam Navigation Company , more commonly known as the White Star Line .
Mildred Jeffrey ( 1910 - -2004 ) was a political and social activist during the labor reforms and civil rights movements .
Ben Garth Mann ( 16 November 1915 in Brandon , Texas -- 11 September 1980 ) was an American baseball player who played pinch runner in the Major Leagues in 1944 .
Klaus Rudolf Werhand ( 4 December 1938 -- 20 March 2009 ) was a German Blacksmith .
Konrad Friedrich Bauer ( 9 December 1903 -- 17 March 1970 ) was a German type designer who , though not related to founder Johann Christian Bauer , was head of the art department for the Bauer Type Foundry from 1928 until his retirement in 1968 .
Christopher Martyn ( c. 1617 -- 26 January 1678 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1646 and 1660 .
Johannes Antiquus ( 1702 Groningen -- 1750 Groningen ) ) was an 18th - century Dutch painter .
Asa Mahan ( 1799 -- 1889 ) was a U.S. Congregational clergyman and educator and the first president of Oberlin College and Adrian College .
Arnald de Grey ( 11 September 1856 -- 15 November 1889 ) was an English cricketer who played one cricket match for the amateur side I Zingari in 1880 .
Shridhar Venkatesh Ketkar ( 2 February 1884 -- 10 April 1937 ) was a sociologist , historian and novelist from Maharashtra , India .
Meyer Abovitz ( מאיר בן ישעיהו אבוביץ ; alternate spelling Meir Abowitz ; born 1876 - died 1941 ) was a Rabbi and Rosh Yeshiva active in Mizrachi in Eastern Europe between the Two World Wars .
Tommaso Nardini ( 1658 -- December 9 , 1718 ) was an Italian priest and painter of the Baroque period , active in his native town .
Barnet Kenyon ( 1850 -- 20 February 1930 ) was a British colliery worker , trade union official and Lib--
Albert Ostman ( circa 1893 -- 1975 ) was a Canadian prospector who reported that he was abducted by a Sasquatch and held captive for six days .
John Roxborough ( aka John Rokysburgh , died 1509 ) was a Master of University College , Oxford , England .
Henry Eeles Dresser ( 9 May 1838 -- 28 November 1915 ) was an English businessman and ornithologist .
Waller Hugh Paton RSA RSW ( 27 July 1828 -- 8 March 1895 ) , was a Scottish landscape artist operational in the second half of the 19th century .
Robert Hampden - Trevor , 1st Viscount Hampden ( 17 February 1706 -- 22 August 1783 ) was a British diplomat at The Hague and then joint Postmaster General .
The Rt Rev Samuel Heaslett ( 1875 - 1947 ) was an Anglican bishop .
Dao Zheng ( 道證法師 ) ( 27 February 1957 -- 18 July 2003 ) was a Buddhist nun from Taiwan , known for her various writings and dharma talks .
Johannes Kerkorrel ( 27 March 1960 -- 12 November 2002 ) , born Ralph John Rabie , was a South African singer - songwriter , journalist and playwright .
Viswanatha Satyanarayana ( 10 September 1895 -- 18 October 1976 ) was born to Sobhanadri and Parvathi in the year 1895 at Nandamuru,(pin 521311 ) Krishna District , Andhra Pradesh .
Halvor Olsen Folkestad ( 28 November 1807 -- 30 September 1889 ) was a Norwegian temporarily appointed councillor of state in interim in 1875 .
Johann Andreas Naumann ( 13 April 1744 -- 15 May 1826 ) was a German farmer and an amateur naturalist .
John Treasure ( 6 June 1924 -- 9 February 2004 ) was a leading figure in the British advertising industry in the 1960s , 70s and 80s .
Michael Malpass ( 1946 - -1991 ) was a sculptor and artist best known for his spheres , which he made from found industrial objects using bandsaw and blacksmithing techniques .
Projections back from dated individuals suggest that Coel Hen lived around AD 350 - -420 , during the time of the Roman departure from Britain .
Ann Hawkshaw ( 14 October 1812 -- 29 April 1885 ) was an English poet .
Gareth Forwood ( 14 October 1945 -- 16 October 2007 ) was a British actor .
W. J. Younger ( 1838 - 1920 ) was an American dentist who performed some of the earliest and most groundbreaking research in the field of periodontology .
Charles John Frederick Lampe ( 1739 -- 10 September 1767 ) was an English composer and organist , and the son of composer John Frederick Lampe and the singer Isabella Lampe ( maiden name of Young ) .
Wang Hong ( 王弘 ) ( 379 - -432 ) , courtesy name Xiuyuan ( 休元 ) , formally Duke Wenzhao of Huarong ( 華容文昭公 ) , was a high - level official of the Chinese dynasty Liu Song .
Ludwig Karl Martin Leonhard Albrecht Kossel ( 16 September 1853 -- 5 July 1927 ) was a German biochemist and pioneer in the study of genetics .
Joseph Bentham ( 1693/94 -- 1671 ) was a Church of England minister at a time , roughly a century after the Breach with Rome , when aspects church doctrine were still relatively unformed .
Sir Peyton Ventris ( November 1645 -- 6 April 1691 ) was an English judge and politician , the first surviving son of Edward Ventris ( d. 1649 ) of the manor of Granhams in Great Shelford , Cambridgeshire , although he was born in Little Wenham , Suffolk .
Prince Leon Aleksander Sapieha ( 1883 - 1944 ) was a Polish military aviator , landowner , traveler , and a member of the Sejm .
Jurjentje Aukes Rauwerda ( 14 December 1812 , in Oentsjerk -- 3 October 1877 , Amsterdam ) , was a Dutch prostitute and procurer .
William Vane , 1st Viscount Vane ( 17 February 1682 -- 20 May 1734 ) , was a British Whig politician .
Celia Winter - Irving ( 1941 -- 26 July 2009 ) , was an Australian - born , Zimbabwean - based artist and art critic who wrote extensively on Zimbabwean art , especially Shona sculpture , when she lived in Harare from 1987 - -2008 .
The Oaten Hill Martyrs ( also known as the `` Canterbury martyrs '' ) were Catholic Martyrs who were executed by hanging , drawing and quartering at Oaten Hill , Canterbury , on 1 October 1588 .
Frederick David Sassoon ( 1 May 1853 -- 4 May 1917 ) was a Anglo - Jewish merchant and banker in Hong Kong and China .
Lipót Fejér ( or Leopold Fejér , Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈfɛjeːr ) ; 9 February 1880 -- 15 October 1959 ) was a Hungarian born Jewish mathematician .
Martha Denny ( 1505 -- 9 January 1572 ) was an aristocratic English woman who was also a recusant and was sent to prison in 1562 for having attended mass . Her husband was Sir Wymond Carew , by whom she had 19 children , including lawyer Sir Matthew Carew .
Domingo Esguerra Plata ( 28 March 1875 -- 1965 ) was a Colombian lawyer who served as Minister of Foreign Affairs of Colombia , Ambassador of Colombia to Brazil , and Ambassador of Colombia to the United Kingdom .
Bartholomew Albizzi ( died 1361 ) was an Italian Franciscan hagiographer .
Titus Fulvius Iunius Macrianus ( died 261 ) , also known as Macrianus Minor , was a Roman usurper .
Alida Chelli ( 23 October 1943 -- 14 December 2012 ) was an Italian actress , singer , and TV - hostess .
Jurij Dalmatin ( c. 1547 -- 31 August 1589 ) was a Slovene Lutheran minister , writer and translator .
Karel Ančerl ( 11 April 1908 -- 3 July 1973 ) was a Czechoslovak conductor , renowned especially for his performances of contemporary music and for his interpretations of music by Czech composers .
Ludovicus a S. Carolo ( secular name Louis Jacob , Latin form Ludovicus Jacob ) ( 20 August 1608 -- 10 March 1670 ) was a French Carmelite scholar , writer and bibliographer .
Brigadier William Mackintosh , Laird of Borlum ( 1658 - -1743 ) usually known as Mackintosh of Borlum was a Scottish soldier and a leader of the Jacobite rising of 1715 and a member of the Clan Mackintosh .
François Willi Wendt ( 16 November 1909 - 15 May 1970 ) was a French non - figurative painter of German origin belonging to the New Ecole de Paris .
Nio Joe Lan ( Chinese : 梁友兰 ; pinyin : Liáng Yǒulán ; Perfected Spelling : Nio Yu Lan ; also known by the Indonesianised name Junus Nur Arif ; 29 December 1904 -- 13 February 1973 ) was a Chinese - Indonesian writer , journalist , and history teacher .
Eachmarcach Ó Catháin ( aka Echlin O'Cahan or Ackland Kane ) , Irish harper and composer , 1720 - 1790 ) .
Matthias Faber , S.J. , ( 24 February 1586 -- 26 April 1653 ) was a German Jesuit priest , who gained fame as a religious writer and preacher .
René Guilleré ( 16 August 1878 -- 24 November 1931 ) was a French lawyer who founded the Ateliers Primavera , which made decorative art objects .
Paul Alexander Bartlett ( 13 July 1909 -- 19 April 1990 ) was an American writer , artist , and poet .
Anton Furst ( 6 May 1944 -- 24 November 1991 ) was a production designer who won an Academy Award for designing the noirish nightmare version of Gotham City in Tim Burton 's Batman ( 1989 ) .
Charles Guillaume Loys de Bochat ( born 11 December 1695 in Lausanne , died 4 April 1754 , also in Lausanne ) was an 18th - century Swiss jurist and antiquarian ( Lausanne at the time was a subject territory controlled by Berne ) .
Herbert George Jenkins ( 1876 -- 8 June 1923 ) was a British writer and the owner of the publishing company Herbert Jenkins Ltd , which published many of P. G. Wodehouse 's novels .
Yosef Kremerman ( Hebrew : יוסף קרמרמן‎ , born 1926 , died 12 November 1981 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Herut , Gahal and Likud between 1964 and 1977 .
Sir Arthur Morse ( Chinese : 摩士 ) ( 25 April 1892 - 13 May 1967 ) was the head of The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation during and after World War II . He was a British banker born in Tipperary in Ireland .
Santasilan Kadirgamar ( Tamil : சாந்தசீலன் கதிர்காமர் ; 11 April 1934 -- 25 July 2015 ; known as Silan Kadirgamar ) was a Sri Lankan Tamil academic , historian and author .
Ernesto Calindri ( 5 February 1909 -- 9 June 1999 ) was an Italian theater and film actor .
Clifford Travis Bean ( 21 August 1947 -- 10 July 2011 , aged 63 ) was an American luthier and machinist from California .
Pedro Alonso Niño ( also Peralonso Niño ) ( 1468 - -c . 1505 ) was a Spanish explorer .
William Leslie Cazneau ( 1807 - -1876 ) was a Texas pioneer and is credited with having buried the Alamo Heroes with full military honors .
Roger Milliot ( 1927 , Le Creusot - 1968 ) was a French poet and painter .
Lubi Kui ( simplified Chinese : 陆费逵 ; traditional Chinese : 陸費逵 ; pinyin : Lùbì Kuí , 17 September 1886 -- 9 July 1941 ) was a Chinese educationist and publisher .
William II of Baux ( died 1239 ) was a son of William of Baux .
Raghunath Bhattacharyya ( died 18 June 2013 ) was an Indian judge .
Ambrozije Kapić ( died 1598 ) served as an Archbishop of Antivari ( Bar ) in the late 16th century .
Maurice Elvey ( 11 November 1887 -- 28 August 1967 ) was the most prolific film director in British history .
English McConnell ( 14 May 1883 -- 13 June 1928 ) was an Irish footballer who played for Sunderland , Chelsea and Ireland as a wing half .
Edward Cock ( 1805 - -1892 ) , British surgeon , was a nephew of Sir Astley Cooper , and through him became at an early age a member of the staff of the Borough Hospital in London , where he worked in the dissecting room for 13 years .
Colonel Winthrop Hilton ( c. 1671 - 1710 ) was the highest - ranking officer in New Hampshire through King William 's War and Queen Anne 's War .
Peter Schlumbohm ( July 10 , 1896 -- 1962 ) was a German inventor , best known for creating the Chemex Coffeemaker .
Sir Denis William Brogan ( born 11 August 1900 in Glasgow ; died 5 January 1974 ) , Scottish author and historian .
James Gillespie ( c. 1747 -- 11 January 1805 ) was a Democratic - Republican U.S. Congressman from North Carolina between 1793 and 1799 .
Xue Ju ( 薛舉 ) ( died 618 ) , formally Emperor Wu ( 武皇帝 , `` Martial '' ) , was the founding emperor of a short - lived state of Qin at the end of the Chinese dynasty Sui Dynasty , whose state was eventually destroyed by Tang Dynasty .
Arthur Leopold Busch or Du Busc ( 5 March 1866 -- 9 March 1956 ) was a British - born American naval architect responsible for the development of the United States Navy 's first submarines .
Pietro Ciriaci ( 2 December 1885 -- 30 December 1966 ) was an Italian Cardinal of the Catholic Church who served as prefect of the Sacred Congregation of the Council in the Roman Curia from 1954 until his death , and was elevated to the cardinalate in 1953 by Pope Pius XII .
Greville Verney , 8th Baron Willoughby de Broke and de jure 16th Baron Latimer ( c1620 - 1648 ) was a peer in the peerage of England .
Morris Keith Hopkins ( 20 June 1934 -- 8 March 2004 ) was a British historian and sociologist .
Elijah Moulton ( 1820 - -1902 ) was a pioneer settler in Los Angeles , California , after the Mexican - American War , and became one of its wealthiest citizens .
Robert Tatton ( 1606 -- 19 August 1669 ) was the High Sheriff of Chester between 1645 and 1646 .
Lethlobar mac Loingsig ( died 873 ) was a Dál nAraidi king of Ulaid , which is now Ulster , Ireland .
Sir Oliver St John , 1st Viscount Grandison ( 1559 - -1630 ) was an English soldier who became Lord Deputy of Ireland .
Gilbert Alsop ( 10 September 1908 -- 16 April 1992 ) was an English professional footballer .
Richard Leach Maddox ( 4 August 1816 -- 11 May 1902 ) was an English photographer and physician who invented lightweight gelatin negative plates for photography in 1871 .
Gaetano Berenstadt ( 7 June 1687 -- buried 9 December 1734 ) was an Italian alto castrato who is best remembered for his association with the composer George Frideric Handel .
Jeremiah Moulton ( b. York , Massachusetts ( now in York , Maine ) , 1688 , d. York , 20 July 1765 ) was a New England militia officer and member of the Massachusetts Council .
Fritz Brun ( 18 August 1878 -- 29 November 1959 ) was a Swiss conductor and composer of classical music .
Maestro António Fortunato de Figueiredo ( 20 August 1903 -- 1981 ) was a famous Goan conductor and violinist .
William Henry Brookfield ( 31 August 1809 -- 12 July 1874 ) was an Anglican priest , Inspector of Schools , and chaplain - in - ordinary to Queen Victoria .
John Billee ( fl . 1873 -- January 16 , 1890 ) was a Creek Indian and an American outlaw of the Old West .
V. Madhavan Nair ( 1915 - -1996 ) more popularly known as Mali Madhavan Nair was a lawyer , journalist , sportsman , musicologist , kathakali playwright , dramatist , editor and a pioneer in radio broadcasting .
Seif el - Din el - Zoubi ( Hebrew : סיף א - דין א - זועבי‎ , Arabic : سيف الدين الزعبي‎ ; 1913 -- 26 June 1986 ) was an Israeli - Arab politician .
Scott Piering ( 13 September 1946 , Duluth , Minnesota -- 24 January 2000 ) was a successful and influential American - born music publicist for many British music acts , including Pulp , The KLF , The Smiths , Stereophonics , The Orb , Placebo , Underworld and The Prodigy .
David Wilder , Jr. ( 3 May 1778 -- 21 September 1866 ) was an American politician who served as the Treasurer and Receiver - General of Massachusetts and as the first Massachusetts Auditor .
Alastair Royalton - Kisch ( 20 January 1920 -- 21 March 1995 ) , known professionally as Royalton Kisch , was an orchestral conductor in London from 1947 to 1964 .
William Playfair ( 22 September 1759 -- 11 February 1823 ) was a Scottish engineer and political economist , the founder of graphical methods of statistics .
Jordi Benito i Verdaguer ( Granollers , 1951 - Barcelona , December 9 , 2008 ) was a Catalan artist .
Richard Beaumont - Thomas died on 14 February 1917 leaving a will of £ 449,285 - 18 - 9 pounds sterling .
Lucy M. Boston ( 1892 - -1990 ) , born Lucy Maria Wood , was an English novelist who wrote for children and adults , publishing her work entirely after the age of 60 .
Albert Alonzo Robinson ( October 21 , 1844 -- 1918 ) , sometimes referred to as Albert A. Robinson or A. A. Robinson , was an American civil engineer who rose through the ranks of the Atchison , Topeka and Santa Fe Railway to eventually become the railroad 's vice president and general manager .
William Moreton ( 1641 -- 21 November 1715 ) was an English prelate in the Church of Ireland who served as the Bishop of Meath from 1705 - 1716 .
Major General Victor Sellheim CB , CMG ( 4 May 1866 -- 25 January 1928 ) was an Australian military officer during the Second Boer War and World War I.
Lord Colin Campbell ( 9 March 1853 -- 18 June 1895 ) was a Scottish Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1878 to 1885 .
Ernst Pringsheim , Sr . , Ernst Pringsheim sen . ( 11 July 1859 , Breslau - 28 June 1917 , Breslau ) was a German physicist .
Henry Ingersoll Bowditch ( 1808 - 1892 ) was an American physician and a prominent Christian abolitionist .
Major David Graham Shillington PC(NI ) ( 10 December 1872 -- 22 January 1944 ) was an Ulster Unionist politician .
Arne Løchen ( 20 November 1850 - 22 August 1930 ) was a Norwegian psychologist , philosopher and literary researcher .
Anchitell Grey ( c. 1624 - 8 July 1702 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in two periods between 1665 and 1695 .
Sir Richard Cox , 1st Baronet PC ( 25 March 1650 -- 3 May 1733 ) was an Irish lawyer and judge .
Sigvatr Þórðarson ( Sighvatr Þórðarson , Sigvat Tordarson ) or Sigvat the Skald ( 995 - 1045 ) was an Icelandic skald .
Harry Hanger ( 1886 -- 23 March 1918 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a centre half .
Guelfo Zamboni ( 1897 - -1994 ) was an Italian diplomat who saved hundreds of Jews during the Holocaust .
John Alexander Jackson ( 1809 -- 25 May 1885 ) was a public servant , colonial agent in pre - Federation Australia and Treasurer of South Australia .
Philip Hugh Padwick R.O.I & R.B.A. ( 1876 - -1958 ) was an English painter noted for his oil landscapes .
Aslak Brekke ( October 6 , 1901 -- 1978 ) was a prominent vocalist of one of the Scandinavian poetic genres that is referred to as stev .
Maja Refsum ( 23 September 1897 -- 11 January 1986 ) was a Norwegian sculptor and teacher .
Eirik Vandvik ( 1904 - 1953 ) was professor in literature at the university of Oslo .
Maurice Strakosch ( probably 15 January 1825 -- 9 October 1887 ) was an American musician and impresario of Czech origin .
Johann Rasso Januarius Zick ( 6 February 1730 -- 14 November 1797 ) was a painter and architect .
Daniel Dumaresq FRS ( 1712 - -1805 ) was an educational consultant to Russian and Polish monarchs Duraresq came from Trinity , Jersey in the Channel Islands .
Alvaro de Loyola Furtado ( died 23 August 1981 ) , was a member of the Goa assembly and a parliamentarian .
Mohit Chattopadhyaya ( also spelled Mohit Chattopadhyay ) ( 1 June 1934 -- 12 April 2012 ) was a Bengali Indian playwright , screenwriter , dramatist and poet .
Tessa Davies ( 1940 -- 1 June 1988 ) was an English set decorator .
Owen Manning ( 1721 - -1801 ) was an English clergyman and antiquarian , known as a historian of Surrey .
Michal Josef Gusikov ( born Yehiel - Michiel , also spelt Guzikow or Gusikow ) ( 2 September 1806 - 21 October 1837 ) was a klezmer who gave the first performances of klezmer music to West European concert audiences on his ' wood and straw instrument ' .
Sir Robert Williams , 9th Baronet ( 20 July 1764 -- 1 December 1830 ) was a British politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1790 to 1830 .
William Basil Jones ( 1 January 1822 - 14 January 1897 ) was a Welsh priest and scholar who became the Bishop of St David 's in 1874 , holding the post until his death in 1897 .
John Rowand ( c. 1787 -- 30 May 1854 ) was a fur trader for the North West Company and later , the Hudson 's Bay Company .
Mathilde Nielsen ( 26 October , 1858 -- 11 September , 1945 ) was a Danish actress in the theatre and in Danish cinema .
George A. Berlinghof ( c. 1862 - -May 30 , 1944 ) was a German - born architect who designed a number of important buildings in Lincoln and other cities in Nebraska .
Emma Cons ( 4 March 1838 -- 24 July 1912 ) was a British social reformer , educationalist and theatre manager .
Şehzade Halil ( probably 1346 - -1362 ) was an Ottoman prince .
Allan Belcher ( 2 December 1884 -- 2 July 1921 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with and coached Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Oleg Slabynko ( ca . 1962 -- 25 January 1996 ) , a Russian , was working for Russian Television Channel 2 as a TV producer for the show `` Moment Istiny '' ( Moment of Truth ) in Moscow , Russia .
Henry II of Niemodlin ( Polish : Henryk II Niemodliński ) ( 1374 -- 22 December 1394 ) was a Duke of Strzelce and Niemodlin since 1382 until his death ( with his brothers as co - rulers and only formally ) .
Otani Nobutomo ( a.k.a . Otani Shimosa no Kami Seiichiro , Otani Shintaro ) ( 1798 - 1864 ) was a Japanese martial artist .
Edward Harley , 3rd Earl of Oxford and Earl Mortimer ( c. 1699 -- 11 April 1755 , in Bath ) was a British peer .
Leonard Colebrook FRS ( 2 March 1883 -- 27 September 1967 ) was an English physician and bacteriologist .
Idriss Miskine ( 15 March 1948 -- 7 January 1984 ) was a Chadian politician and diplomat under Presidents Félix Malloum and Hissène Habré .
Hasan Gafoor ( 11 December 1950 -- 12 March 2012 ) was the Director General of Police of Maharashtra ( Anti Corruption bureau ) .
Henry St. John Thackeray ( 1869 - -30 June 1930 ) was a British biblical scholar at King 's College , Cambridge , an expert on Koine Greek , Josephus and the Septuagint .
Sir Richard Vernon , 3rd Baronet ( 22 June 1678 -- 1 October 1725 ) was a British diplomat and politician .
Farrukhzad ( Middle Persian : Farrūkhzādag ; New Persian : فرخزاد ) , was an Iranian aristocrat from the House of Ispahbudhan and the founder of the Bavand dynasty , ruling from 651 to 665 .

Grenfell `` Gren '' Jones MBE ( 13 June 1934 -- 4 January 2007 ) was one of Wales 's best - known and longest - serving newspaper cartoonists .
Carl O'Neil Little ( 17 December 1938 -- 6 August 2005 ) , better known by his stage name Carlo Little , was a rock and roll drummer , based in the London nightclub scene in the 1960s .
Giles Heron ( by 1504-August 1540 ) was an English politician .
Chungnyeol of Goryeo ( 3 April 1236 -- 30 July 1308 ) ( r. 1274 - -1308 ) was the 25th ruler of the medieval Korean kingdom of Goryeo .
Florimond Van Duyse ( 4 August 1843 -- 18 May 1910 ) was a Belgian lawyer , composer and musicologist .
John F. A. Sanford ( 1806 - -1857 ) was a frontiersman of the American west who worked with Native American tribes as an Indian agent .
Adam Muszka ( b. Piotrków Trybunalski 4 March 1914 ; d. Paris January 2005 ) was a Polish - French painter and sculptor , representing in his works distinctive elements of Jewish life in pre - war Poland and post - war western Europe .
Nicolas Pineau ( 1684 - -1754 ) was a French carver and ornamental designer , one of the leaders who initiated the exuberant asymmetrical phase of the high Rococo .
George Kruger Gray ( 25 December 1880 -- 2 May 1943 ) was an English artist , best remembered for his designs of coinage and stained glass windows .
George Granville Slack ( 11 July 1906 - -30 November 2003 ) , known as Granville Slack , was a British judge and Liberal politician .
Albert Pissis ( 1852 - 1914 ) was the architect who introduced the Beaux - Arts architectural style to San Francisco , California , designing a number of important buildings in the city in the years before and after the 1906 San Francisco earthquake .
Jeremy Silberston ( 1 April 1950 - -9 March 2006 ) , was an English film director .
Marriott Edgar ( 1880 - -1951 ) , born George Marriott Edgar in Kirkcudbright , Scotland , was a poet , scriptwriter and comedian best known for writing many of the monologues performed by Stanley Holloway , particularly the ' Albert ' series .
Emma Smith DeVoe ( 1848 - -1927 ) was a leading Women Suffragist in the early twentieth century , changing the face of politics for both women and men alike .
( Agnes ) Elisabeth Lutyens , CBE ( 9 July 1906 -- 14 April 1983 ) was an English composer .

Tom Goddard ( 1 October 1900 -- 22 May 1966 ; in full Thomas William John Goddard or simply Thomas William Goddard ) was the fifth highest wicket taker in first - class cricket .
Lü Ju ( died 256 ) , courtesy name Shiyi ( 世議 ) , was a military general of the state of Eastern Wu during the Three Kingdoms period .
Hildebrand Gregori , O.S.B. Silv . , ( 8 May 1894 -- 12 November 1985 ) , was an Italian Benedictine monk , who served as the Abbot General of the Sylvestrine congregation of the Order .
William Humble ( later William John Humble - Crofts ; 9 December 1846 -- 1 July 1924 ) was an English clergyman and cricketer who played for Derbyshire between 1873 and 1877 .
Sir John Phillips Rhodes , 2nd Baronet , DSO ( 19 July 1884 -- 14 November 1955 ) was the son of Sir George Rhodes , a Justice of the Peace for Cheshire .
Brigadier - General Percy Robert Clifford Groves CB CMG DSO ( 26 May 1878 -- 12 August 1959 ) was a senior British air strategist who served in the British Army and the Royal Air Force .
Pierre Dumas ( died Paris , 29 February 2000 ) was a French doctor who pioneered drug tests in the Olympic Games and cycling .
Leonel Power ( also spelled Lionel , Lyonel , Leonellus , Leonelle ; Polbero ; 1370 to 1385 -- 5 June 1445 ) was an English composer of the late Medieval and early Renaissance eras .

Douglas Keith Carmody ( 16 February 1919 -- 21 October 1977 ) was an Australian first - class cricketer who played during the 1940s and 1950s .

George Home , 1st Earl of Dunbar , KG , PC ( ca . 1556 -- 20 January 1611 ) was , in the last decade of his life , the most prominent and most influential Scotsman in England .
Rachel Trickett ( 20 December 1923 -- 24 June 1999 ) was an English novelist , non‑fiction writer , literary scholar , and a prominent British academic ; she served as Principal of St Hugh 's College , Oxford for nearly twenty years , between 1973 and 1991 .
Morton Birnbaum ( 1926 - 2005 , Brooklyn ) was an American lawyer and physician who advocated for the right of psychiatric patients to have adequate help , and who coined the term sanism .
Walt Carmon ( 1894 - 1968 ) was a magazine editor and writer best known for his years as managing editor of the Communist magazine the New Masses from 1929 to 1932 .
Alexander Viets Griswold Allen , D.D. ( 1841 - -1908 ) was an Episcopal theologian , born at Otis , Massachusetts , United States of America .

Edmund Goulding ( 20 March 1891 -- 24 December 1959 ) was a British film writer and director .

Laurie Cahill ( 22 September 1912 - 6 December 1974 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for South Adelaide in the South Australian National Football League ( SANFL ) and Richmond in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Aage Thaarup ( 1906 - -1987 ) was a Danish - born milliner who ran a celebrated hatmaking business in London between the 1930s and 1970s .
Raymond E. Page ( 1895 - -1992 ) was a Southern California - based landscape architect , best known for his work at Pickford , the Beverly Hills home of Mary Pickford and Douglas Fairbanks .

Alan Steen ( 1922 -- 26 August 2012 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a winger , active between 1939 and 1952 .

William Crofts , 1st Baron Crofts ( c.1611 - -1677 ) was an English baron and Gentleman of the Bedchamber to Charles II .

John Horsefield ( 18 July 1792 -- 6 March 1854 ) was an English handloom weaver and amateur botanist after whom the daffodil Narcissus ' Horsfieldii ' is named .

Walter Spies ( 15 September 1895 -- 19 January 1942 ) was a Russian - born German primitivist painter .
Peter Scawen Watkinson Roberts VC , DSC ( 28 July 1917 -- 8 December 1979 ) was an English recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .

Octavius Oakley RWS ( 27 April 1800 , in Bermondsey -- 1 March 1867 , in London ) , was an English watercolour portrait , figure and landscape artist .
Martin Dumollard ( 22 June 1810 − 8 March 1862 ) was a French serial killer condemned to the guillotine after having been arrested and charged with the deaths of maids from 1855 to 1861 .
Feliks Oraczewski of Szreniawa coat of arms ( 14 January 1739 in Przybysławice -- 12 August 1799 in Vienna ) was a Polish writer , educational and political activist .

Witold Rodziński ( 5 October 1918 -- 18 December 1997 ) was a Polish historian , sinologist and diplomat .
Reverend Geoffrey Lowrey Speak ( 史璧琦牧師 ) OBE ( 6 October 1924 -- 13 March 2000 ) was a British teacher and educationist to Hong Kong .
Famed locally for his philanthropy , he died on 10 September 1579 , leaving money in his will to establish the Richard Watts Charity and Six Poor Travellers House in Rochester High Street .
John Hawley Edwards ( 21 March 1850 -- 14 January 1893 ) was an English footballer who made one appearance for England in 1874 , before going on to play for Wales in 1876 .
Karl Ludwig Hencke ( 8 April 1793 -- 21 September 1866 ) was a German amateur astronomer .
Pathani Samanta ( /pəthɑːnɪ sɑːməntə/ ; Odia : ପଠାଣି ସାମନ୍ତ born Samanta Chandra Sekhar Harichandan Mahapatra ; 13 December 1835 - 11 June 1904 ) was an Indian astrologer and scholar who measured the distance from earth with a bamboo pipe and many other traditional instruments that he built .
Nancy Burne ( 23 December 1907 , Chorlton , Lancashire -- 25 March 1954 ) was an English stage and film actress .
Huangfu Bo ( 皇甫鎛 ) ( died 820 ) was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reign of Emperor Xianzong .

Vaughan Murray Griffin ( 1903 - -1992 ) was an Australian print maker and painter .

Gofraid mac Sitriuc ( died 951 ) , in Old Norse Guðrøðr Sigtryggsson , was King of Dublin .
François Sébastien Letourneux ( 1752 - -1814 ) was a French lawyer and politician who was Minister of the Interior under the Directory .
Joan Fitzgerald , Countess of Ormond , Countess of Desmond ( ca . 1509 or ca . 1514 -- 2 January 1565 ) was a Norman - Irish noblewoman and heiress , a member of the Fitzgerald family , who were also known as the `` Geraldines '' .
Georges Burou ( 1910 - -1987 ) was a French gynecologist who managed a clinic in Casablanca , Morocco and is widely credited with innovating modern sex reassignment surgery for trans women .
Michael Arne ( 1740 or 1741 -- 14 January 1786 ) was an English composer , harpsichordist , organist , singer , and actor .
Palmer Williams ( died Jan. 1 , 1996 ) was an American broadcast journalist and documentary film maker .
Sydney George Hulme Beaman , born in 1887 and who died 4 February 1932 , was an author & illustrator best known as the creator of the Toytown stories and their characters including Larry the Lamb .
Louise Dickinson Rich ( 14 June 1903 -- 9 April 1991 ) was a writer known for fiction and non - fiction works about the New England region of the United States , particularly Massachusetts and Maine .
Alois Wotawa ( 11 June 1896 -- 12 April 1970 ) was an Austrian composer of chess problems and endgame studies .
Jaya Prakash Malla ( Nepali : जयप्रकाश मल्ल ) ( died 1768 ) was the last king of Yen ( यें ) or Kantipur ( कान्तिपुर ) which corresponds to present day Kathmandu .
Li Baoyu ( 李抱玉 ) ( 703 -- April 15 , 777 ) , né An Chongzhang ( 安重璋 ) , known for some time as An Baoyu ( 安抱玉 ) , formally Duke Zhaowu of Liang ( 涼昭武公 ) , was a general of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty .
Don Branigan ( 1933 - -1999 ) was a Canadian politician and medical doctor , best known as a former mayor of Whitehorse , Yukon .
Joaquín Ascaso Budria ( Zaragoza , c. 1906/1907 -- Caracas , March 1977 ) was an anarcho syndicalist and President of the Regional Defence Council of Aragon between 1936 and 1937 .
John de Pembroke ( died 1365 ) was a Welsh - born judge who held several senior offices in Ireland , including that of Chancellor of the Exchequer of Ireland .
Zhao Xinchu ( Chinese : 赵辛初 ) ( 1915 - -1991 ) , birth name Shuai Qitai ( Chinese : 帅启汰 ) or Shuai Yinghai ( Chinese : 帅英孩 ) , courtesy name Qitai ( Chinese : 启泰 ) , was a Chinese politician , born in Huangmei County , Hubei Province .
Cecil Frances Alexander ( April 1818 -- 12 October 1895 ) , was a hymn - writer and poet .
Friedrich August von Klinkowström ( 31 August 1778 -- 4 April 1835 ) was a German artist , author and teacher from an old Pomeranian noble family .
Christian Vater ( 11 October 1679 -- 25 January 1756 ) was a German organ and harpsichord builder .
George W. Drum ( October 3 , 1925 - -December 16 , 1997 ) was an early leader in automobile club circles , and the first director of the Crosley Car Owners Club in 1952 .
Leif Rustad ( 30 October 1903 -- 17 June 1976 ) was a Norwegian cellist and radio pioneer .
Thomas Lipson , R.N. ( ca.1784 -- 25 October 1863 ) generally known as Captain Lipson was born in Dartmouth , England .
Yolanda Mérida ( 20 August 1929 -- 11 April 2012 ) was a Mexican actress known for her work in theater and television .
Ștefan Bârsănescu ( 28 March 1895 - -5 November 1984 ) was a Romanian academician and educator who gained renown as an essayist and philosopher .
Johann Freiherr von Appel ( also Baron Johann von Appel ) , ( 1826 -- 1906 ) was an Austrian administrator .
Gerd Aretz ( born 18 February 1930 , died 5 July 2009 ) was a German artist .
George Leeman ( August 1809 -- 25 February 1882 ) was a lawyer , railwayman and a Liberal Member of Parliament ( MP ) for the City of York in the nineteenth century .
Alfonso de Bourbon Sampedro ( born Leon Shafferman ; 22 October 1932 -- 10 January 2012 ) , known as The Count , was a Swiss - American eccentric who claimed to be a descendant of the Spanish Royal Family and a first cousin of King Juan Carlos .
Andrew Melville ( 1 August 1545 -- 1622 ) was a Scottish scholar , theologian and religious reformer .
Alexander Grinberg ( Александр Данилович Гринберг , Aleksandr Danilovich Grinberg ) ( 1885 - -1979 ) was a Russian and Soviet photographer .
Monroe Berkowitz ( 1919 - -2009 ) was Professor of Economics at Rutgers University , New Brunswick , New Jersey , where he was chair for many years , and director of the Bureau of Economic Research .
Colonel John Suther Williamson CB ( ca . 1775 - -26 April 1836 ) was a British Army officer who served in the Royal Artillery during the Napoleonic Wars .
Reverend Thomas Kingsmill Abbott ( 26 March 1829 -- 18 December 1913 ) was an Irish scholar and educator .
Publius Licinius Cornelius Saloninus Valerianus ( c. 242 -- 260 ) was Roman Emperor in 260 .
Galal Amer ( Arabic : جلال عامر‎ ; 23 July 1952 -- 12 February 2012 ) was an Egyptian journalist , well known for his sarcasm and sense of humor .
Wilson Barrett ( born William Henry Barrett ; 18 February 1846 -- 22 September 1904 ) was an English manager , actor , and playwright .
Helgi Jónsson ( 11 April 1867 , Rangárvallasýsla - 1925 ) was an Icelandic botanist and phycologist .
Mario Visintini , MOVM , ( 26 April 1913 -- 11 February 1941 ) , was the first Regia Aeronautica ace of World War II . In recognition of his flying skill and meticulousness , Visintini was nicknamed cacciatore scientifico ( scientific fighter pilot ) .
Doug Munro ( 7 February 1917 -- 18 September 1989 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
George Bull ( 25 March 1634 -- 17 February 1710 ) was an English theologian and Bishop of St David 's .
Camille Gutt ( 14 November 1884 -- 7 June 1971 ) , born Camille Guttenstein , was a Belgian economist , politician , and industrialist .
Countess Johanna Magdalene of Hanau - Lichtenberg ( 18 December 1660 , Bischofsheim am Hohen Steg -- 21 August 1715 , Hanau ) was a daughter of Johann Reinhard II of Hanau - Lichtenberg ( 1628 - -1666 ) and the Countess Palatine Anna Magdalena of Birkenfeld - Bischweiler ( 1640 - -1693 ) .
Wilhelm August Graah ( 1793 - -1863 ) was a Danish naval officer and Arctic explorer .
Anthony Freston , né Brettingham ( 1757 - -1819 ) was an English Anglican clergyman .
Fazal Mahmood ( Urdu : فضل محمود‎ ) , ( 18 February 1927 -- 30 May 2005 ) was a Pakistani cricketer , regarded as the finest pace bowler of his country 's early years .
Michael Darbyshire ( 15 October 1917 -- 20 November 1979 ) was an English television actor most famous for his portrayal of Hubert Davenport , the Victorian ghost in the long - running BBC TV children 's comedy series Rentaghost .
Hugh of Champlitte ( died 1209 ) was the nephew of William of Champlitte , the first Prince of Achaea .
Karelius August Arntzen ( 10 November 1802 -- 1876 ) was a Norwegian jurist , civil servant and politician .
István Thomán ( Hungarian : ( ˈiʃtvaːn ˈtomaːn ) ; 4 November 1862 -- 22 September 1940 ) was a Hungarian piano virtuoso and music educator .
Edward Grainger ( 1797 - -1824 ) was an English teacher of anatomy , and dresser to Sir Astley Cooper .
Pandit Wamanrao Sadolikar ( 16 September 1907 -- 25 March 1991 ) was a Hindustani classical vocalist of the Jaipur - Atrauli Gharana founded by his guru , Utd .
Franz Bardon ( 1 December 1909 -- 10 July 1958 ) was a Czech occultist and student and teacher of Hermetics .
Friedrich Seyler ( 13 December 1642 -- 31 January 1708 ) , also spelled Friedrich Seiler , was a Swiss Reformed ( i.e. Calvinist ) pastor and theologian from Basel , noted for his work Anabaptista Larvatus on Anabaptism .
Herb Louch ( 4 January 1875 -- 29 August 1936 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Charles Valentine Le Grice ( 1773 - -1858 ) was an Anglican priest , an associate of Charles Lamb and Samuel Taylor Coleridge , a squib writer , and a translator of Longus .
James Thurbarne ( 1607 - -1688 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1656 and 1679 .
Ernest J. Kump , Jr. ( December 29 , 1911 -- November 4 , 1999 ) , was an American architect , author , and inventor based in Palo Alto , California .
Sir Maurice Denys ( 1516 - -1563 ) of St John 's Street , Clerkenwell , London and Siston Court , Gloucestershire , was an English lawyer in London and a property speculator during the Dissolution of the Monasteries , during which period he served as a `` powerful figure at the Court of Augmentations '' .
Dame Alice Josephine Mary Taylor Barnes , DBE ( 18 August 1912 -- 28 December 1999 ) , known professionally as Dr. Josephine Barnes , was a leading obstetrician and gynaecologist .
Richard Gwent ( died 1543 ) , was the archdeacon of London .
François van Campenhout ( 5 February 1779 -- 24 April 1848 ) was a Belgian opera singer , conductor and composer .
Pierre Laporte ( 25 February 1921 -- 17 October 1970 ) was a Canadian lawyer , journalist and politician who was the Deputy Premier and Minister of Labour of the province of Quebec before being kidnapped and assassinated by members of the group Front de libération du Québec ( FLQ ) during the October Crisis .
Jack Chanin ( 1907 - -1997 ) was a performer , demonstrator , manufacturer , creator , and magic shop owner .
SS - Gruppenführer Fritz Katzmann or Friedrich Katzmann ( 6 May 1906 -- 19 September 1957 ) was a Nazi German Major General and Polizei leader who perpetrated genocide in Katowice , Radom , Lemberg ( Lwów ) , Danzig ( Gdańsk ) , and across the Nazi German District of Galicia during the Holocaust in occupied Poland .
Mullamangalath Raman Bhattathiripad ( 1908 - -2001 ) , commonly known as M. R. Bhattathiripad or MRB , was a social reformer , cultural leader and a Malayalam writer .
Domenico Bellizzi ( 1918 - 1989 ) , also known under the pseudonym of Vorea Ujko , is among the most popular and respected of the Arbëresh poets .
John Francis Neylan ( November 6 , 1885 - August 19 , 1960 ) was an American lawyer , journalist , political and educational figure .
Derek Richter ( 14 January 1907 -- 15 December 1995 ) , English neuroscientist , was one of the founding fathers of the science of brain chemistry .
Jakob Edelstein ( AKA Yacov , Yaakov , Jakub Edelstein or Edlstein ) , ( Horodenka ( Galicia ) , 25 July 1903 -- 20 June 1944 Auschwitz ) was a Czechoslovakian Zionist , social democrat and the first Jewish Elder in the Theresienstadt ghetto
Tahir Tewfiq ( Kurdish : تایەر تۆفیق‎ , Arabic : طاهر توفیق‎ , also Tayer Tofiq ) ( 1922 - -1987 ) was a popular Kurdish musician and singer .
Diego Fernández de Cáceres y Ovando ( -- Monleón , aft . February 2 , 1487 ) was a Spanish military and nobleman .
Sir Howard Elphinstone , 2nd Baronet ( 9 June 1804 -- 16 March 1893 ) was a British Whig politician He was elected as Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Hastings at the 1835 general election , having unsuccessfully contested the seat in 1832 .
Arthur Fleischmann ( born 1896 , Bratislava ; d. 2 March 1990 , Tenerife ) was a Slovak - born , London - based sculptor , who pioneered the use of Perspex in sculpture .
Jeanne Weber ( 7 October 1874 -- 5 July 1918 ) was a French serial killer .
Giuseppe Filippo Liberati Marchi ( 1735 -- 2 April 1808 ) was an Italian - English painter and engraver .
Thomas Davison ( 1794 - 1826 ) was a British radical journalist and printer - publisher of a series of journals , including Medusa , the London Alfred , the Deist 's Magazine , as well as the James Griffin - edited Cap of Liberty and the Robert Shorter - edited Theological Comet .
Richard Harding Watt ( 1842 - -1913 ) was an English designer who worked with four professional architects to create large houses and associated buildings in the town of Knutsford , Cheshire .
Anna Juliana Gonzaga , O.S.M. , ( 16 November 1566 -- 3 August 1621 ) was an Archduchess of Austria who became a Religious Sister of the Servite Order after the death of her husband , the Archduke Ferdinand II of Austria .
Ivan Belostenec ( born in Varaždin , ca . 1594 - Lepoglava , died 2 February 1675 ) was a Croatian linguist and lexicographer .
June Ravenhall ( 1901 - -1984 ) is one of the British Heroes of the Holocaust .
Thomas Prothero ( or Protheroe ) ( 1780 - -1853 ) was a Welsh lawyer and businessman , known as an opponent of John Frost and a mine owner .
Gilbert Basset ( died 1241 ) was an English baronial leader during the reign of King Henry III .
Henry Heyward Isham ( 4 November 1926 - 18 June 2009 ) , was a negotiator who played an important role in the talks with North Vietnam that led to the Peace accord of 1973 .
John E. Hamm , M.D. ( 31 May 1776 , in Kent Co. , near Dover , Delaware -- 22 March 1864 , in Zanesville , Muskingum Co. , Ohio ) was an American US Army colonel , doctor and politician , diplomat , industrialist , and Marshall of the State of Ohio during the War of 1812 .
Salimuzzaman Siddiqui ( Urdu : سلیم الزّماں صدّیقی‎ ( səˈliːmʊzzəmɑːn sɪˈd̪d̪iːqi ) ; 19 October 1897 -- 14 April 1994 ) , HI , MBE , SI , DPhil , FPAS , FRS , was a Pakistani organic chemist , versatile scholar , and a leading scientist in the natural product chemistry .
Luis Martínez Griñán ( 16 February 1917 -- 17 September 1990 ) , better known as Lilí Martínez , was a Cuban pianist , arranger and composer specializing in the son montuno style .
Balthasar Coyett ( c.1650 Fort Zeelandia ( Taiwan ) -- 19 September 1725 , Batavia , Dutch East Indies ) was a Dutch - Swedish official in the Dutch East India Company , serving from 1701 to 1706 as the Governor of Ambon .
Giovanni Andrea Tria ( 22 July 1676 -- 16 January 1761 ) , was an Italian bishop , diplomat and historian .
Maurice McCrackin ( 1905 - -1997 ) was an American civil rights and peace activist , tax resister and Presbyterian minister .
Michel Boudart ( born 18 June 1924 in Brussels , Belgium ; died 2 May 2012 ) PhD was the William M. Keck Sr . Professor of Chemical Engineering Emeritus at Stanford University .
Matthew Talbot Baines QC , DL ( 17 February 1799 -- 22 January 1860 ) was a British lawyer and Liberal politician .
Andrianjaka reigned over the Kingdom of Imerina in the central highlands region of Madagascar from around 1612 to 1630 .
Izidor Cankar ( 22 April 1886 -- 22 September 1958 ) was a Slovenian author , art historian , diplomat , journalist , translator , and liberal conservative politician .
John Clifford Heed ( 1862 - -1908 ) was an American composer and musician , best known for composing over 60 marches .
Benno Vigny ( 28 October 1889 -- 31 October 1965 ) was a French - German novelist and screenwriter .
Henry Otis Dwight , LL.D. ( June 3 , 1843 -- June 19 , 1917 ) , was an American missionary and author .
Carleton Wiggins NA ( 1848 - -1932 ) was an American landscape and cattle painter .
Ron Kingston ( 10 October 1931 -- 15 March 1997 ) was an Australian rules footballer , who played in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Miguel Caldera ( 1548 - -1597 ) was an important figure in the pacification and colonization of Mexico 's northern frontier immediately following the Spanish conquest of the Aztec Empire .
John Fitzedmund Fitzgerald ( died 1589 ) was the hereditary Seneschal of Imokilly ( Imokilly is the area around Youghal , both words deriving from Eochaill , meaning a yew wood ) , an Irish nobleman of the originally Welsh - Norman FitzGerald dynasty in the province of Munster .
Colonel Sir Joseph West Ridgeway GCB GCMG KCSI PC ( Ire ) ( 16 May 1844 -- 16 April 1930 ) was a British civil servant and colonial governor .
Lord James Beauclerk ( c. 1709 -- 20 October 1787 ) was an Anglican clergyman who served as the Bishop of Hereford from 1746 to 1787 .
Albert G. Richards ( 1917 - 2008 ) was a photographer and dental scientist .
Timothy Priestley ( 19 June 1734 -- 23 April 1814 ) was an English Independent minister .
Giani Gurdit Singh ( 24 February 1923 -- 17 January 2007 ) was born in Mithewal village ( Sangrur district ) in the state of Punjab , India .
Inamullah Khan ( 1912 - -1997 ) was a Muslim activist who symbolised the World Muslim Congress , Al - Motamar al - Alam al - Islami , for almost four and half decades .
Mary Rosse , Countess of Rosse ( née Mary Field ) ( 1813 - 1885 ) , was a British amateur astronomer and pioneering photographer .
Henri Admirat ( 3 September 1744 -- 17 June 1794 ) was a notable figure in the French Revolution .
Henry Torrens Anstruther ( 27 November 1860 -- 5 April 1926 ) was a British Liberal Unionist politician .
Sir Thomas Deane ( Cork , 1792 -- Dublin , 1871 ) was an Irish architect .
Athanasios Psalidas ( Greek : Αθανάσιος Ψαλίδας ; 1767 - -1829 ) , was a Greek author , scholar and one of the most renowned figures of the modern Greek Enlightenment .
Sir Cedric Stanton Hicks ( 2 June 1892 - 7 February 1976 ) was an Australian Professor of Human Physiology and Pharmacology at the University of Adelaide .
Samuel Azu Crabbe ( 18 November 1918 -- 15 September 2005 ) was a barrister , solicitor and jurist .
Richard Nugent , 3rd Earl of Westmeath , born before 1669 , died April 1714 .
John Gibson Paton ( 24 May 1824 -- 28 January 1907 ) , born in Scotland , was a Protestant missionary to the New Hebrides Islands of the South Pacific .
At the age of 52 , having been hospitalized after a stroke , Uthum Herat died on 23 October 2009 at a private hospital in Colombo .
David Louis Band or David L. Band ( 9 January 1957 -- 16 March 2009 ) was an astronomer , a leading scientist in theory of the gamma - ray bursts .
Kotogahama Sadao ( Jap 琴ヶ濵貞雄 ) ( 10 October 1927 - 7 June 1981 ) was a sumo wrestler from Kanonji , Kagawa , Japan .

Per Øyvind Heradstveit ( 26 May 1932 -- 11 May 2004 ) was a Norwegian television journalist and non - fiction writer .
Carl Ditters von Dittersdorf ( 2 November 1739 -- 24 October 1799 ) was an Austrian composer , violinist and silvologist .
William Michell ( 14 February 1796 -- 4 November 1872 ) was a British physician and Member of Parliament .
Frans Otto Eriksson ( 15 April 1867 -- 7 June 1953 ) , also known as Svarta Hästen ( `` The Black Horse '' ) , was a Swedish baker and a convicted thief and murderer .
Captain John Wallace Thomas CBE ( 1888 - -1965 ) was a Newfoundland merchant mariner who served with distinction in the First and Second World Wars .
Valentin Markin ( aka `` Arthur Walter '' ) ( 1903 -- 1934 ) was the chief illegal rezident and director of the espionage operations of the Soviet Union in the United States from 1933 to 1934 .
Francesco Antonio Caneti ( 1652 - -1721 ) was an Italian miniature painter of the Baroque period .
Herbert Mayo , M.D. ( 3 April 1796 -- 28 June 1852 ) , was a British physiologist , anatomist and medical writer .
Thomas Percival Montague Mackey ( 1 June 1894 -- 23 November 1950 ) , better known as Percival Mackey , was a British pianist , composer and bandleader .
Ovid died at Tomis in AD 17 or 18 .
George Sussum ( 1803 -- 10 August 1882 ) was an English cricketer who was associated with Cambridge Town Club and made his first - class debut in 1827 , playing at that level until 1832 .
Ratu Tevita Vakalalabure ( 1927 -- 6 May 2005 ) was a Fijian chief and politician .
Lykele Faber , also given as Lijkele Faber ( Koudekerk aan den Rijn , 14 September 1919 - Vernon , British Columbia , 3 October 2009 ) was a Dutch commando and radio operator during World War II . He took part in the Battle of Arnhem and helped organize the Dutch resistance .
Sir Nicholas Williams , 1st Baronet ( 1681 -- 19 July 1745 ) was a British politician .
Karl Wilhelm Wefring ( 11 October 1867 -- 28 September 1938 ) was a Norwegian physician and politician who served as Minister of Defence in the 1920s .
Horace Day ( 3 July 1909 -- 24 March 1984 ) , also Horace Talmage Day , is a painter of the American scene , born in China , who came to maturity during the Thirties and was active as a painter over the next 50 years .
Mona Salyer Lambird ( 1938 - -1999 ) was an Oklahoma lawyer who became the first woman president of the Oklahoma Bar Association and the first woman elected to the Board of Governors of the Oklahoma Bar Association .
Chief Pretty Eagle ( 1846 - -1903 ) was a war chief , warrior , and diplomat of the Crow Nation .
Yang Kui ( Chinese : 楊逵 ; Wade -- Giles : Yang K'uei ; 18 October 1906 -- 12 March 1985 ) was a prominent writer in Taiwan under Japanese rule .
Gour Khyapa ( 15 August 1947 -- 26 January 2013 ) was a Bengali Baul singer and a philosopher .
Luis Alberto Acuña Gatillon ( 1927 in Iquique -- 2005 ) was a Chilean writer and storyteller par excellence born in Iquique .
Milorad Drašković ( Serbian Cyrillic : Милорад Драшковић ; 10 April 1873 -- 21 July 1921 ) was a Serbian politician who was the Minister of Internal Affairs of the Kingdom of Yugoslavia .

Adalla of Silla ( died 184 , r. 154 - -184 ) was the eighth ruler of Silla , one of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Major Greenwood FRS ( 9 August 1880 -- 5 October 1949 ) was an English epidemiologist and statistician .
Thomas Vilhelm Garde ( 22 October 1859 -- 24 June 1926 ) was a Danish naval officer , distinguished for his explorations in Greenland .
Lavinia Spencer , Countess Spencer ( née Bingham ; 1762 -- 1831 ) , was a British illustrator .
Maria Lanc ( born Maria Jenewein ; 1911 -- 15 November 1995 ) was an Austrian humanitarian .
Thomas Letts ( 1803 -- 1873 ) was an English stationer and printer who popularised the diary .
William Longshaw , Jr. ( 26 April 1836 -- 15 January 1865 ) was a British - born physician who served in the United States Union Navy during the American Civil War .
Juan Díaz de Solís ( 1470 -- 20 January 1516 ) was a 16th Century navigator and explorer .
Beryl Patricia Hall , née Woodhouse ( 1917 - -2010 ) ( cited in ornithological literature as B.P. Hall and in self - published works as Pat Hall ) , was a British ornithologist , associated with the Natural History Museum .
Ray Rosso ( 1916 - 1 December , 2012 ) was an Italian - born American football coach and Orange Coast College 's first ever football coach .
Ferdiš Duša ( 13 January 1888 in Frýdlant nad Ostravicí -- 1958 ibidem ) was a Czech folk painter , graphic artist , illustrator and manufacturer of ceramics , coming from the borderland between Moravia and Silesia .
Professor Armando Menezes ( 1902 - -1983 ) was a Goan poet , writer , academic and civil servant .
Johan Helo ( 22 August 1889 , Helsinki - 25 October 1966 ; surname until 1906 Helenius ) was a Finnish lawyer , diplomat and politician .
William Bower Dawes ( c. 1807 -- 3 August 1869 ) was a farmer in the colony of South Australia , and member of the first fully elected House of Assembly .
Tetsu Komai ( 1894 - -1970 ) was a Japanese actor , known for his minor roles in Hollywood films .
Sir Rowland Hayward ( c. 1520 -- 5 December 1593 ) was a London merchant , and Lord Mayor of the City in both 1570 and 1591 .
Giovanni Battista Benaschi , or Beinaschi , ( 1636 - -1688 ) was an Italian painter and engraver active in the Mannerist style .
Daniel Mendaille ( 27 November 1885 - 17 May 1963 ) was a French stage and film actor whose career spanned nearly sixty years .
Abner Dean ( 18 March 1910 -- 30 June 1982 ) , born Abner Epstein in New York City , was an American cartoonist who was the nephew of sculptor Jacob Epstein .
William Douglas Mackenzie , D.D. , LL.D. ( July 16 , 1859 -- 1936 ) was an American Congregational theologian , born at Fauresmith , Orange River Colony , South Africa , educated in Edinburgh at Watson 's College School ( 1875 ) and at the Congregational Theological Hall ( 1880 - -82 ) .
Thomas Walter Williams ( 1763 - -1833 ) was an English barrister , known as a legal writer .
Erik Balling ( 29 November 1924 -- 19 November 2005 ) was a Danish TV and film director .
Friedrich Lutz ( 22 February 1852 in Heidenheim -- 14 May 1918 in Oettingen ) was a German politician , Bavarian brewery owner , and farmer .
Camillo Filippi ( died 1574 ) was an Italian painter who flourished about the middle of the 16th century .
Zhang Fei ( died 221 ) , courtesy name Yide , was a military general who served under the warlord Liu Bei in the late Eastern Han dynasty and early Three Kingdoms period .
Allan Surtees ( 31 December 1924 -- 1 November 2000 ) was an English actor who appeared in many television productions and films over a 30-year period .
Sayyid Zainal Abidin Ali Khan Bahadur was the son of Nawab Nazim Ashraf Ali Khan of Bengal by his Mut``ah wife , Sharaf - un - nisa Khanum . He died in February , 1826 at Murshidabad .
Joseph Alexander Ames ( 1816 - -1872 ) was an American artist , primarily known for portrait and genre painting .
Roger Martival ( died 14 March 1330 ) was a medieval Bishop of Salisbury in England .
Shiv Kumar Patel ( died 22 July 2007 ) , also known as Dadua , was a notorious dacoit ( bandit ) who operated in ravines and forests on the borders between the Indian states of Uttar Pradesh and Madhya Pradesh .
Barthélémy Djabla ( 1936 -- 15 September 2008 ) was the Ivorian Archbishop of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Gagnoa , based in Gagnoa , Côte d'Ivoire .
Lydia Longley ( Sainte - Madeleine ) ( 1674 -- 20 July 1758 ) , is known to many as `` The First American Nun '' after Helen A. McCarthy Sawyer of Groton , Massachusetts published her biographical novel written for Roman Catholic children , The First American Nun , in 1958 .
Stewie Speer ( Stewart Speer , 26 June 1928 -- 16 September 1986 ) was an Australian jazz and rock drummer who is best known as a member ( 1967 - -1976 , 1980 ) of the Australasian group Max Merritt and the Meteors .
Gerald Vere Borlase Burgoyne born 1900 and died 4 July 1943 .

Clifford Grobstein ( July 20 , 1916 -- September 6 , 1998 ) was an American biologist , a cancer researcher , a member of the National Academies of Sciences .
Leslie Perri ( died 1970 ) was the pen name of Doris Marie Claire `` Doë '' Baumgardt , an American science fiction fan , writer , and illustrator .

Robert Goldsand ( March 17 , 1911 -- September 16 , 1991 ) was an Austrian - American classical pianist .
Samuel Rowlands ( c. 1573 - -1630 ) was an English author of pamphlets in prose and verse , which reflect the follies and humours of the lower middle - class life of his time .
William Van Duzer Lawrence ( 1842 - -1927 ) was a millionaire real - estate and pharmaceutical mogul who is best known for having founded Sarah Lawrence College in 1926 .
Abi Williams ( died 1963 ) was a Welsh nationalist who briefly served as the President of Plaid Cymru .
John E. Fenton ( 1898 - 1974 ) was a judge and president of Suffolk University in Boston , Massachusetts from 1965 to 1970 .
Basilio Álvarez ( 1877 - 1943 ) was a Spanish priest , journalist and politician related to the Galician agrarianist movement .
Zhang Renjie ( Chinese : 張人傑 ; Wade -- Giles : Chang Jen - chieh ; 19 September 1877 − 3 September 1950 ) , born Zhang Jingjiang ( Chinese : 張靜江 ; Wade -- Giles : Chang Ching - chiang ) , was a political figure and financial entrepreneur in the Republic of China .
