José Medel ( June 21 , 1938 - January 31 , 2001 ) , sometimes introduced as Joe Medel , was a Mexican boxer in the Featherweight division .

Megasphaeroceras is an ammonite genus included in Sphaeroceratidae , a family of ammonoid cephalopods characterized by their sphaeroidal shells with markedly eccentric coiling , fine ribbing , and complex sutures , known from the lower middle Jurassic .

Robert Arrigo ( born December 4 , 1954 , in Sliema ) is a Maltese politician currently a Member of the House of Representatives of Malta for the Government .

Tshering Tobgay ( born 19 September 1965 ) is a Bhutanese politician who has been the Prime Minister of Bhutan since 2013 .

James McNeill ( 27 March 1869 -- 12 December 1938 ) was an Irish politician and diplomat , who served as first High Commissioner to London and second Governor - General of the Irish Free State .

Giovanni Francesco Barbarigo ( 1658 at Venice -- 1730 ) was an Italian cardinal and nephew of Saint Gregorio Barbarigo ( 1625 - -97 ) .

Alomia is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae , described as a genus in 1818 .

Dytiscus caraboides is a species of beetle from the Dytiscidae family .

Myriophyllum simulans is a species of water milfoil native to southeastern Australia where it grows in aquatic habitat such as ponds and streams , as well as muddy or swampy soil .
The Polyporaceae are a family of bracket fungi belonging to the Basidiomycota .
Libythea cinyras was a species of butterfly in the nymphalid Libytheinae subfamily .
Hemilepistus reaumuri is a species of woodlouse that lives in and around the deserts of North Africa and the Middle East , `` the driest habitat conquered by any species of crustacean '' .
Ixinandria steinbachi is the only species in the genus Ixinandria of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Loricariidae .
Berberis arguta is a shrub in the Berberidaceae described as a species in 1908 , having been first described in 1886 at the `` forma '' level .
Achatinella pupukanioe is a species of land snail , a gastropod in the Achatinellidae family .
Boltonia diffusa ( smallhead doll 's daisy ) is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
The jewelled blenny , Salarias fasciatus , is a popular marine aquarium fish species in Australasia .
The Cichlinae are a subfamily of South American fishes in the cichlid family .

Heteropyxis is a genus which includes three species of small evergreen trees .
Picea critchfieldii , the Critchfield 's spruce , is a species of spruce that went extinct in the Late Quaternary extinction event .

Marsupidium epiphytum is a liverwort species in the genus Marsupidium from the New Zealand .

Lipographis umbrella is a species of snout moth in the genus Lipographis .
Trematosaurus is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian found in Germany and Russia .
Sinorhizobium americanum is a bacterium first isolated from root nodules of Acacia species native of Mexico .
Silvanerpeton is an extinct genus of early reptiliomorph found in East Kirkton Quarry of West Lothian , Scotland , in a sequence from the Brigantian substage of the Viséan ( Lower Carboniferous ) .
Triplosarus novaezelandiae is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Triplosarus .
Alpinia zerumbet , commonly known as shell ginger , is a perennial species of ginger native to East Asia .
Chapalmalania is an extinct procyonid genus from the Pliocene of South America , which lived from 5.3 to 1.8 million years ago .
Afrotyphlops schlegelii , commonly known as Schlegel 's beaked blind snake or Schlegel 's giant blind snake , is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Alopecosa ovalis is a species of wolf spider found in Inner Mongolia in the People 's Republic of China .
Trichocentrum , often abbreviated Trctm in horticulture , is a genus in the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Rhinella icterica ( common name : yellow cururu toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae that is found in northeastern Argentina ( Misiones Province ) , southern Brazil , and eastern Paraguay .
Lobochilotes labiatus is a species of fish endemic to Lake Tanganyika .
Hydroscapha is a genus of beetles endemic to Europe and the United States .
Ficimia is a genus of colubrid snakes commonly known as hooknose snakes or hook - nosed snakes , which are endemic to North America .
Clionella sinuata , common name the ribbed turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Clavatulidae .
Eccremocarpus scaber , the Chilean glory - flower , is a species of perennial plant in the Bignoniaceae family .
Schiedea haleakalensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name Haleakalā schiedea .
Xenostylus sublineatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Xenostylus .
Accuminulia is a genus of moths belonging to the family Tortricidae .
Orthodontopsis bardunovii is a species of moss in the family Orthodontiaceae .
Pectinatus is a genus of Firmicutes bacteria classified within the class Negativicutes .
Bulbophyllum absconditum , known as the ' Hidden Bulbophyllum , is a species of orchid in the genus Bulbophyllum .
Milichiidae are a family of flies .
Cirsonella microscopia is a species of extremely small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Skeneidae .
As the physiological and anatomical difference between the two was so great , the subclass Archaeornithes was erected for the latter .
Dolabella auricularia , common name the `` wedge sea hare '' or `` Donsol '' in the Philippines , is a species of large sea slug , a marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Aplysiidae , the sea hares .

Dentectus barbarmatus is the only species of the monotypic genus Dentectus , a genus of armored catfish .
The Golden Yellow - flowered Dendrobium ( Dendrobium chrysanthum ) is a species of orchid .
Gagea divaricata is an Asian species of plants in the lily family , native to Kazakhstan , Kyrgyzstan , Tajikistan , Uzbekistan , and Xinjiang Province of western China .
Diplogasterida was formerly an order of nematodes .
Viola alba ( commonly known as white violet ) is a species of violet in the family Violaceae .
Episoriculus is a genus of shrew in the red - toothed shrew subfamily .
Ictiocyon is an extinct genus of large , mostly carnivorous bone - crushing mammals known as bear dogs , of the family Amphicyonidae endemic to Asia during the Miocene living from 23.03 - -15.97 Ma and existed for approximately 7.06 million years .
The American cheetah ( Miracinonyx ) is an extinct genus of at least two feline species , which were endemic to North America during the Pleistocene epoch ( 2.6 Ma -- 12,000 years ago ) and morphologically similar to the modern cheetah .
It contains only one species , Delairea odorata , which was previously included in the genus Senecio as Senecio mikanioides , and is known as Cape ivy in some parts of the world and German ivy in others .
Deinacrida elegans is a species of weta in family Anostostomatidae .
Babesia ( also called Nuttallia ) is a genus of protozoan apicomplexan piroplasms which was discovered by the Romanian bacteriologist Victor Babeș , that infect the blood and cause a parasitic , hemolytic disease known as babesiosis .
Lascoria aon is a species of litter moth of the Erebidae family ..
Hackelia velutina is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name velvet stickseed .
Wendlandia exserta ( Ukan Pansara in Pakistan ) , ( Simtaaraa in Nepal ) is an evergreen tree species in the Rubiaceae family .
Conophytum is a genus of South African and Namibian succulent plants that belong to the Aizoaceae family .
Allium maximowiczii is an Asian plant species native to Siberia , the Russian Far East , Mongolia , Japan , Korea and northeastern China ( Heilongjiang , Jilin and Inner Mongolia ) .
Poecilocapsus lineatus also known as Fourlined Plant Bug , is a species of bugs from Miridae family that are native to the United States .
Lygosoma singha ( Sri Lankan supple skink or Taylor 's skink ) is a species of skink endemic to island of Sri Lanka .
Abactochromis is a monotypic genus of cichlid fish containing the single species Abactochromis labrosus ( formerly known as Melanochromis labrosus ) .
The Eurybrachidae ( sometimes spelled `` Eurybrachyidae '' or `` Eurybrachiidae '' ) are a small family of planthoppers with species occurring in parts of Asia , Australia and Africa .
Argyrotaenia ivana , the Ivana Leafroller Moth , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
The shah kuli ( Alburnus sellal ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Alburnus .
Aplexa rivalis is a species of small air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Physidae , a family which are sometimes known as the bladder snails .
Stenoseris is a genus of Asian plants in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Trimeresurus macrops is a venomous pit viper species endemic to Southeast Asia .
Crataegus anamesa , the Fort Bend Hawthorn , is a species of hawthorn that is endemic to Texas , in North America .
Ernolytis chlorospora is a species of sedge moths , and the only species in the genus Ernolytis .
Haplopelma is a genus of old - world tarantula found in Southeast Asia .
Labrisomus nuchipinnis , the hairy blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Atlantic Ocean from the coast of the Americas to the African coast .
Phlaocyon yatkolai is an extinct species of canid mammal known from the early Hemingfordian ( 20.4 to 16 million years ago ) Runningwater Formation , Box Butte County , Nebraska ( 42.2 ° N 103.1 ° W , paleocoordinates 42.9 ° N 99.2 ° W ) .
Dimocarpus australianus also known as Australian Native Lychee , is a species of trees , closely related to the longan , constituting part of the plant family Sapindaceae .
Dwardius is an extinct genus of otodontid sharks which existed during the Cretaceous period in what is now Australia , England , France , and India .
Theloderma corticale ( common names : mossy frog , Vietnamese mossy frog , and Tonkin bug - eyed frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Tyrannomyrmex is a rare tropical genus of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Erythroxylum ecarinatuma is a Southwest Pacific and Australian species of Erythroxylum .
Menura tyawanoides is an extinct species of lyrebird from the Early Miocene of Australia .
Sutilizona tunnicliffae is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Sutilizonidae .
Megacephala helmsi is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Blackburn in 1892 , and is endemic to Australia .
Argonauta absyrtus is an extinct species of octopus assigned to the genus Argonauta .
Euphorbia helioscopia ( sun spurge ) is a species of spurge native to most of Europe , northern Africa , and eastward through most of Asia .
Symmoriida is an extinct order of sharks that contains three families .
Xenurobrycon polyancistrus is a freshwater fish , the smallest species of characin in its family and order .
Cycas brunnea is a species of cycad in the genus Cycas , native to northern Australia in northwest Queensland and northeast Northern Territory in a small area straddling the border of the two regions .
The Anelloviridae are a recently discovered family of viruses .

Dichochrysa is a genus of green lacewings .

Palaeotringa is a prehistoric bird genus that was discovered by O. C. Marsh during the bone wars .
Hyracodontidae is an extinct family of rhinoceroses endemic to North America , Europe , and Asia during the Eocene through early Miocene living from 55.8 - -20 mya , existing for approximately 35.8 million years .

Acupicta is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) are found in the Indomalaya ecozone and the Australasian ecozone .

This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Anzina carneonivea .

Stigmatochromis woodi is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it can be found hunting for prey over sandy areas .

Stanhopea stevensonii is a species of orchid endemic to Colombia ( Meta ) .

Blechnum procerum , commonly known as mountain kiokio or small kiokio , is a species of fern found in New Zealand .
Cirripectes variolosus , the red - speckled blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the Pacific ocean .
Ophthalmoptera longipennis is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Ophthalmoptera of the family Ulidiidae .
Miltonia moreliana is a species of orchid occurring in Brazil ( southeastern Bahia to northern Espírito Santo ) .
The Danaini are a tribe of brush - footed butterflies ( family Nymphalidae ) .
Dosinia anus , common name the ringed dosinia , is a species of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae , the venus clams .
Aenictus fergusoni is a species of reddish brown army ant found in Bangladesh , India , Myanmar , Nicobar Islands , Thailand , Vietnam , and China .
Dasysyrphus pauxillus is a North American and European species of hoverfly .
Weinmannia spiraeoides was a species of plant in the Cunoniaceae family .
Lambdoceras is an extinct genus of Protoceratidae belonging to the order Artiodactyla ( subfamily Synthetoceratinae ) endemic to North America during the Miocene , living epoch 20.6 - -13.6 Ma , existing for approximately 7 million years .
Gecatogomphius is an extinct genus of Middle Permian captorinid with multiple tooth rows known from the Kirov Oblast and the Republic of Tatarstan of Russia .
The Caatinga cacholote ( Pseudoseisura cristata ) is a species of bird in the Furnariidae family .
Resupinatus applicatus , commonly known as the smoked oysterling or the black jelly oyster , is a species of fungus in the family Tricholomataceae , and the type species of the genus Resupinatus .
Strumaria barbarae is a species of plant that is native to Namibia and to Cape Province in South Africa .
Sarcodon squamosus is a species of fungus in the genus Sarcodon .
Lithodes galapagensis is a species of king crab identified in 2009 which lives around the Galapagos Islands , in warm water .
The Thick - spurred Bulbophyllum ( Bulbophyllum crassipes ) is a species of orchid .
Limnocyon is a genus of hyaenodontid creodont that lived in North America during the middle Eocene , existing for approximately 10 million years .
Burnupia crassistriata is a species of small freshwater snail or limpet , an aquatic gastropod mollusk which was traditionally placed in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails and their allies .
Trochidrobia is a genus of very small freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Tateidae .
Tetheamyrma is a genus of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae containing the single species Tetheamyrma subspongia .
Trichostema austromontanum is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name San Jacinto bluecurls .
Pitcairnia spectabilis is a species in the genus Pitcairnia .
Fusiturris similis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Clavatulidae .
Polypterus congicus , the Congo bichir , is a species of bichir with a maximum recorded size of 970 mm ( 39 `` ) .
Guancha philippina is a species of calcareous sponge from the Philippines .
Brevicipitidae or rain frogs is a small family of frogs , which as of November 2013 contains 34 species in 5 genera .
Mertensophryne lindneri ( common names : Dar es Salaam toad , Lindners toad , Lindners dwarf toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Agonum cupreum is a species of ground beetle from the family Platyninae .
Paralamiodorcadion schmidi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paralamiodorcadion .
Crambus alienellus is a species of moth of the family Crambidae .
Thyreus is an Old World genus of bees , one of many that are commonly known as cuckoo bees , and are cleptoparasites of other species of bees , mostly in the genus Amegilla .
Celastrina is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae found in the Palearctic , Nearctic , Indomalayan and Australasian ecozones .
Poecilia sphenops is a species of fish , of the genus Poecilia , known under the common name molly ; to distinguish it from its congeners , it is sometimes called short - finned molly or common molly .
Oenopota pyramidalis , common name the pyramid lora , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mangeliidae .
Ernstichthys anduzei is a species of banjo catfish endemic to the Orinoco River basin of Venezuela .
Carex hirtifolia , the pubescent sedge , is a species of sedge native to north - eastern North America .
Taenioides is a genus of gobies native to fresh , brackish and marine waters of the coastal areas of the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Hoplopholcus forskali is a cellar spider species found from Eastern Europe to Turkmenistan .
Canis cedazoensis is an extinct species of smaller Canidae which was endemic to North America from the Blancan stage of the Pliocene epoch through the Irvingtonian stage of the Pleistocene epoch living 4.9 Ma--300,000 years ago .
Gnaphosa alpica is a ground spider species found in Europe .
Alcantarea imperialis is a species of bromeliad in the genus Alcantarea .
The Atherospermataceae , commonly known as the southern sassafrases , are a family of broadleaf evergreen trees and shrubs .
Cremnophila pyraustella is a species of snout moth in the genus Cremnophila .
Nephrotoma is a genus of crane flies .
Sorbus leptophylla , the thin - leaved whitebeam , is a species of plant in the Rosaceae family .
Bidens cabopulmensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Sebastes rubrivinctus is a species of fish in the rockfish family found in the Eastern Pacific
Aplysiopsis is a genus of sacoglossan sea slugs , a shell - less marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Hermaeidae .
Stephanorrhina is a genus belonging to the Scarabaeidae family , Cetoniinae subfamily , tribe Goliathini .
Omeisaurus ( meaning `` Omei lizard '' ) is a genus of sauropod dinosaur from the Middle Jurassic Period ( Bathonian - Callovian stage ) of what is now China .
Microseris nutans is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name nodding microseris .
Ischnochiton cariosus , commonly known as the Corroded Ischnochiton is a species of chiton in the Ischnochiton genus that lives under rocks in the intertidal and shallow subtidal waters of southern Australia and up the coast of Western Australia as far as Shark Bay .
Abralia astrosticta is a species of enoploteuthid cephalopod present in the waters of Australia , French Polynesia , Japan , New Zealand , the Philippines and Hawaiʻi .
Due to a lack of known major threats to the species , the IUCN redlist currently lists the Western Atlantic finless eel as Least Concern .
Asclepias eriocarpa is a species of milkweed known by the common names woollypod milkweed , Indian milkweed , and kotolo .
The Malayan porcupine or Himalayan porcupine ( Hystrix brachyura ) is a species of rodent in the family Hystricidae .
Mallotus thunbergianus is a species of evergreen plant in the Euphorbiaceae family .
Regaliceratops is a genus of herbivorous ceratopsid dinosaur that lived during the late Cretaceous period , about 68 million years ago ( Mya ) in what is now Canada .
Passiflora viridescens is a plant species native to Perú and Ecuador .
Pachycondyla is a ponerine genus of ants found in the Neotropics .
Allocota aurata is a species of either blackish - green or brownish - green coloured ground beetle in the Lebiinae subfamily that can be found in such Asian countries as China , Japan , Laos , Nepal , Taiwan ( Formosa ) and Viet Nam .
Pethia didi is a species of cyprinid fish which has only been recorded in the vicinity of Myitkyina and Indawgyi Lake in the north of Myanmar .
Valonia ventricosa , also known as `` bubble algae '' and `` sailors ' eyeballs '' , is a species of algae found in oceans throughout the world in tropical and subtropical regions .
Tucanti plumicornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Tucanti .
Roblinella agnewi is a species of small land snail in the family Charopidae .
Hyotherium is an extinct genus in the pig family .
The Texas toad ( Anaxyrus speciosus ) is a species of medium - sized ( to 9 cm ( 3.5 in ) ) toad that occurs in the southern United States and northern Mexico .
Placidochromis is a genus of cichlids endemic to Lake Malawi in Eastern Africa .
Cryptantha crassipes is a rare species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name Terlingua Creek cat's - eye .
The subfamily Vespinae contains the largest and best - known eusocial wasps , including true hornets ( the genus Vespa ) , and the `` yellowjackets '' ( genera Dolichovespula and Vespula ) .
Ecsenius oculus , known commonly in Micronesia as the Ocular blenny and as the Coral blenny on Christmas Island , is a species of combtooth blenny in the genus Ecsenius .
Prionotus carolinus , commonly known as the northern sea robin , common sea robin or gurnard , is a species of ray - finned fish found in shallow water on the east coast of the United States .
Garrya wrightii is a species of flowering plant in the family Garryaceae known by the common names Wright 's silktassel , quinine - bush , coffee berry , bearberry , feverbush , and grayleaf dogwood .
Pinctada fucata , the Akoya pearl oyster , is a species of marine bivalve mollusk in the family Pteriidae , the pearl oysters .
Nyctegretis cullinanensis is a species of snout moth in the genus Nyctegretis .
Dictyna tullgreni is a species of spider in the Dictynidae family .
Perdicella fulgurans is an extinct species of tropical , tree - living , air - breathing , land snail , arboreal pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Achatinellidae .
Kylix halocydne is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Drilliidae that lives in a tropical climate , usually in the Eastern Pacific area .
Olyra collettii is a species of longtail catfish .
Methylomonas scandinavica is a species of Gram - negative gammaproteobacteria found in deep igneous rock ground water in Sweden .
Masdevallia teaguei is a species of orchid in the genus Masdevallia .
Microbacteriaceae is a family of bacteria of the order Actinomycetales .
Taxus fuana is a species of conifer in the yew family Taxaceae family .
Aloe bakeri is a species of flowering plant in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , native to Madagascar .
Procambarus franzi , the Orange Lake cave crayfish , is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
Cavolinia tridentata is a species of sea butterfly , a floating and swimming sea snail or sea slug , a pelagic marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cavoliniidae .
Malacoctenus zacae , the Zaca blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Pacific coast of Mexico from Baja California to Acapulco .
The Shiny Crystal Dendrobium ( Dendrobium crystallinum ) is a species of orchid .
Mongolbittacus is an extinct genus of hangingfly in the family Bittacidae and containing a single species Mongolbittacus daohugoensis .
Munditia mayana , common name May 's munditia , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk , in the family Liotiidae .
Quercus laurina is a Mexican species of trees in the Fagaceae .
Borassus aethiopum is a species of Borassus palm from Africa .
Palaeoloxodon namadicus or the Asian straight - tusked elephant , was a species of prehistoric elephant that ranged throughout Pleistocene Asia , from India ( where it was first discovered ) to Japan , where the indigenous Neolithic cultures hunted that particular subspecies for food .
Gelidium amansii is an economically important species of red algae commonly found in the shallow coast ( 3 to 10 meters or 10 to 33 feet of depth below the water ) of many east Asian countries including North and South Korea , China , Japan , and Singapore .
Uvanilla olivacea , common name the blood - spotted star shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Allium unifolium , the one - leaf onion or American garlic , is a North American species of wild onion .
Ptilosarcus gurneyi , the orange sea pen or fleshy sea pen , is a species of sea pen in the family Pennatulidae .
Brychius hornii is a species of beetle in the genus Brychius that was first described by George Robert Crotch in 1873 .
Astrolepis cochisensis is a species of fern known by the common name Cochise scaly cloak fern .
Mictyris longicarpus , the light - blue soldier crab , is a species of crab that lives on sandy beaches from the Bay of Bengal to Australia ; with other members of the genus Mictyris , it is `` one of the most loved crabs in Australia '' .
Ipomoea carnea , the pink morning glory , is a species of morning glory .
Leptotyphlops rufidorsus , or the Rose blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Cratogeomys is a genus of rodent in the family Geomyidae .
Pleiospilos is a genus of succulent flowering plants of the Aizoaceae family , native to South Africa .
Clepsis virescana , the light brown apple moth , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Awaous lateristriga , the West African freshwater goby , is a species of goby found in marine , fresh and brackish waters ( though mostly in freshwaters ) along the Atlantic coast of Africa from Senegal to the Cunene River , Angola and also from islands in the Gulf of Guinea .
Asteropseidae is a family of sea stars .
†'Partula raiatensis was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Ginkgo cranei is an extinct Ginkgo species in the family Ginkgoaceae described from a series of isolated fossil ovulate organs and leaves .
Chitron mniszechi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Chitron .
Orontium wolfei is an extinct golden - club species in the family Araceae described from a series of isolated fossil leaves .
Thryptomene hyporhytis is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae .
Coelotilapia joka is a species of cichlid fish from Sierra Leone and Liberia in West Africa .
Discus macclintocki is a species of land snail in the family Discidae known commonly as the Iowa Pleistocene snail and Pleistocene disc .
Floscopa mannii is a species of plant in the family Commelinaceae .
Ethmophyllum was a genus of Cambrian sponge .
Nebria nana is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Qinghai province of China , and Tibet .
Fissurisepta manawatawhia is a species of keyhole limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Fissurellidae .
Eupatorium pilosum , rough boneset , is a rare North American species of plant in sunflower family .
Conus mus , common name the mouse cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Suberites ficus is a species of sponge in the family Suberitidae .
Megachile albisecta is a species of leafcutter bee in the family Megachilidae .
Cualabaea is a genus of prehistoric coelacanth fish which lived during the Jurassic period .
Phyllodus is an extinct genus of fish from the Eocene .
Amanita daucipes is a species of fungus in the Amanitaceae family of the Agaricales order of mushrooms .
Carausius morosus ( the ' common ' , ' Indian ' or ' laboratory ' stick insect ) is a species of Phasmatodea ( phasmid ) that is often kept by schools and individuals as pets .
Turiasaurus ( meaning `` Turia lizard '' ; Turia is the Latin name of Teruel ) is a genus of sauropod dinosaurs .
Iris cathayensis is a beardless iris in the genus Iris , in the subgenus Limniris and in the Tenuifoliae series of the species .
Oriaethus longicornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Oriaethus .
Uromastyx alfredschmidti , commonly known as the ebony mastigure , Schmidt 's mastigure , or Schmidt 's spiny - tailed lizard , is a species of lizard in the family Agamidae .
Palvennia is an extinct genus of ophthalmosaurid ichthyosaurian known from the uppermost Jurassic of Central Spitsbergen , Norway .
Aglaomorpha novoguineensis is a species of ferns in the Polypodiaceae family .
Clinopodium glabellum , the glade calamint , is a species of flowering plant in the mint family .
Antillogorgia bipinnata , the bipinnate sea plume , is a species of colonial soft coral , a sea fan in the family Gorgoniidae .
Prodiplocynodon is an extinct genus of basal crocodyloid crocodylian .
Embernagra is a genus of finch - like tanagers .
Laeliinae is a Neotropical subtribe including 40 orchid genera , such as Brassavola , Laelia , Sophronitis , and Cattleya .
The single known species , Neogaeornis wetzeli , was described from fossils found in the Campanian to Maastrichtian Quiriquina Formation of Chile .
Papilio thuraui is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Tanzania , Malawi , Zambia and Congo Republic .
The Indian stingless bee or dammar bee , Tetragonula iridipennis , is a species of bee belonging to the family Apidae , subfamily Apinae .
Magosternarchus is a genus of weakly electric knifefish in the family Apteronotidae , containing two species .
Acadagnostus is a genus of trilobite from the Middle Cambrian , with 7 species currently recognized .
Acanthocephalus dirus is a species of parasitic worm in the Echinorhynchidae family .
Dactylorhiza incarnata , the early marsh - orchid , is a perennial , temperate - climate species of orchid generally found growing in wet meadows , and generally on base - rich soils , up to about 2100 m asl .
Achyranthes is a genus of medicinal and ornamental plants in the amaranth family , Amaranthaceae .
Anomaloglossus ayarzaguenai ( in Spanish : sapito ninera de Ayarzaguena ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Cnesterodon is a genus of poeciliids native to South America .
Fukuititan is a genus of titanosauriform sauropod dinosaur that lived in the Early Cretaceous ( Barremian age ) in what is now Japan .
Blepharomyia is a genus of tachinid flies in the family Tachinidae .
Incilius canaliferus , also known as the dwarf toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Brunnera macrophylla ( Siberian bugloss , great forget - me - not , heartleaf ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Boraginaceae , native to the Caucasus .
Eucephalus engelmannii is a North American species in the aster fammily known by the common name Engelmann 's aster .
Leptochloa dubia is a species of grass known by the common names green sprangletop and zacate gigante .
The Chatham penguin ( Eudyptes chathamensis ) was a species of penguin , now extinct .
Prionolepis ( meaning `` saw scale '' ) is a genus of prehistoric fish .
Agapanthia frivaldszkyi is a species of beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily , that can be found in Syria and Turkey .
Empididae is a family of flies with over 3,000 described species occurring worldwide in all the Ecozones but the majority are found in the Holarctic .
The Chthamalidae are a family of chthamaloid barnacles , living entirely in intertidal / subtidal habitats , characterized by a primary shell wall of eight , six , or four plates , lacking imbricating plate whorls , and either membraneous or more rarely calcareous basis .
Dugesia hepta is a species of freshwater triclad endemic to Sardinia .
Bothrostethus annulipes is a species of Coreidae family , subfamily Pseudophloeinae .
Praealticus margaritatus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the eastern central Pacific ocean , around Samoa .
Allium sacculiferum is an East Asian species of wild onion native to Japan , Korea , eastern Russia ( Amur Oblast , Khabarovsk , Primorye ) , and northeastern China ( Inner Mongolia , Heilongjiang , Jilin , Liaoning ) .
Festuca subulata is a species of grass known by the common names bearded fescue and nodding fescue .
Hypselobarbus jerdoni , also known as Jerdon 's carp , is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to India where it is found in larger streams of southern Karnataka , Tamil Nadu , Kerala and Maharashtra .
It contains only one known species , Vallariopsis lancifolia , native to Peninsular Malaysia , Borneo , and Sumatra .
Xestia maculata is an owlet moth species found in North America , where it has been recorded from western Canada and Montana .
Rubus arvensis , the field blackberry , is an uncommon North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Castilleja applegatei is a species of Castilleja known by the common names Applegate 's Indian paintbrush and wavyleaf Indian paintbrush .
Parahoplitidae is an extinct family of Cretaceous ammonites with stoutly ribbed , compressed , generally involute shells lacking or with only minor tubercles included in the Deshayestaceae , a superfamily now separated from the Hoplitacaceae .
Wallichia triandra is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family that is native to South Tibet in China and also to the neighboring Arunachal Pradesh region of India .
Plectocomiopsis is a dioecious genus of flowering plant in the palm family found in Indochina , Malaysia , Borneo and Sumatra .
Cricetulodon is an extinct genus of muroid rodent named in 1965 .
Eucalyptus melanophloia , commonly known as Silver - leaved Ironbark , is a species of Eucalyptus which is native to New South Wales and Queensland in Australia .
Arceuthobium monticola is a species of dwarf mistletoe known as western white pine dwarf mistletoe .
Pietschellus is an extinct genus of enigmatic bony fish which existed in northern Italy during the early Eocene epoch ( Ypresian age ) .
Capsospongia is a middle Cambrian sponge genus known from 2 specimens in the Burgess shale .
Dyckia rariflora is a species in the genus Dyckia endemic to the State of Minas Gerais in Brazil .
Antipodocottus galatheae is a species of sculpin found on the continental shelf around New Zealand .
Nomada adusta , is a species of bees belonging to the family Apidae .
Sarothrocera lowii is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Sarothrocera .
Glomerida is an order of pill - millipedes found primarily in the Northern Hemisphere .
Truebella is a genus of true toads native to Peru at Ayacucho and Junín regions .
Glyceria is a widespread genus of grass family common across Eurasia , Australia , North Africa , and the Americas .
Berosus pugnax is a species of hydrophilid beetle native to the United States .
Quercus copeyensis is a species of oak endemic to the Talamancan montane forests of Costa Rica and Panama .
Canistrum camacaense is a species of bromiliad of the genus Canistrum .
Moluccella is a genus of annual and short - lived perennial plants native to Central + southwestern Asia and the Mediterranean .
Mahgarita stevensi is a genus of adapiform primate that lived in North America during the late Eocene .
The Commerson 's anchovy ( Stolephorus commersonnii ) , also known as Devis 's anchovy , Long - jawed anchovy , Teri anchovy , is a species of anadromous fish in the Engraulidae family .
Coryanthes , commonly known as Bucket Orchids , is a genus of tropical epiphytic orchids .
Beaudouin 's snake eagle ( Circaetus beaudouini ) is a species of snake eagle in the Accipitridae family found in the Sahel region of west Africa .
Phacelia formosula is a rare species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name North Park phacelia .
Tchangmargarya multilabiata is a species of large operculate freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Viviparidae , the river snails .
Helicia australasica , also named Austral oak or creek silky oak , is a species of rainforest trees , and constitutes part of the flowering plant family Proteaceae .
Eulithidium affine , common name the polka - dot pheasant or the spotted pheasant , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phasianellidae .
Indirana chiravasi ( Amboli leaping frog ) is a species of frog from the Western Ghats of India .
Grusonia parishii ( Orcutt ) Pinkava is a species of cactus known by the common names matted cholla and Parish club cholla .
Macropodia rostrata , common names , the common spider crab , long - legged spider crab , long - legged crab , is a species of marine crab in the family Inachidae .
Capsella bursa - pastoris , known by its common name shepherd's - purse because of its triangular , purse - like pods , is a small ( up to 0.5 m ) annual and ruderal species , and a member of the Brassicaceae or mustard family .
Pseudotothyris is a genus of armored catfishes native to South America .
Skenella edwardiensis is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Cingulopsidae .
Nebo flavipes is a species of scorpions in the family Diplocentridae .
Corymbia is a genus of about 113 species of tree that were classified as Eucalyptus species until the mid-1990s .
The Syngnathiformes are an order of ray - finned fishes that includes the pipefishes and seahorses .
Yabeinosaurus is an extinct genus of lizard from the Early Cretaceous Jehol Group of northeastern China .
Amphicyon ( `` ambiguous dog '' ) is an extinct genus of large carnivorous bone - crushing mammals , popularly known as bear - dogs , of the family Amphicyonidae , subfamily Amphicyoninae , from the Aquitanian Epoch until the early Pleistocene .
Udubidae is a family of araneomorph spiders , most of whose members were formerly placed in the family Zorocratidae , which is no longer accepted .
Kourisodon is an extinct genus of mosasaur .
Galium hypotrichium is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common name alpine bedstraw .
Galium tricornutum is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common names rough corn bedstraw , roughfruit corn bedstraw , and corn cleavers .
Sinustrombus sinuatus , common name the lacinate conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Psednotrichia is a genus of Angolan flowering plants in the groundsel tribe within the sunflower family .
Gillellus uranidea , the Warteye stargazer , is a species of sand stargazer native to the Atlantic coast of southwestern Florida , USA , and in the Caribbean Sea from the Bahamas and the coast of Central America to Panama where it can be found in sandy areas on reefs or among rocks .
Pagurus bernhardus uses shells of a number of gastropod species for protection , including Littorina littorea , Littorina obtusata , Nassarius reticulatus , Gibbula umbilicalis , Nucella lapillus and Buccinum .
Chascotheca neopeltandra is a species of plants in the family Phyllanthaceae described as a species in 1904 .
Blenniella chrysospilos , the Red - spotted blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian oceans .
Hypselobarbus kurali is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Hypselobarbus .
Citrus micrantha is a species of wild citrus of subgenus Papeda native to southern Philippines , particularly islands of Cebu and Bohol .
Pitcairnia burle - marxii is a species of the bromeliad genus Pitcairnia .
Abraliopsis felis is a species of enoploteuthid cephalopod found in cool temperate water of the north Pacific Ocean .
Lasioglossum aulacophorum , also known as the Lasioglossum ( Sudila ) aulacophorum , is a species of bees in the genus Lasioglossum , of the family Halictidae .
Marleyimyia xylocopae is a species of bee fly from South Africa that has a similarity to the patterning of a carpenter bee Xylocopa flavicollis ( De Geer ) found in the region .
Tortula ruralis , commonly known as twisted moss and star moss , is a species of moss with a cosmopolitan distribution .
Palisota flagelliflora is a plant species endemic to Cameroon .
Meiacanthus bundoon , the Bundoon blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny from the Pacific Ocean where it is known from Fiji and Tonga .
Tabebuia oligolepis is a species of plant in the Bignoniaceae family .
It contains only one species , Hodebertia testalis , and is found in the tropics , but ranges north to parts of Europe on occasion .
Auriscalpium vulgare , commonly known as the pinecone mushroom , the cone tooth , or the ear - pick fungus , is a species of fungus in the family Auriscalpiaceae of the order Russulales .
Gigantopecten latissimus is a species of fossil scallop , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Pectinidae , the scallops .
Plakobranchidae is a family of sea slugs , marine opistobranch gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Plakobranchoidea .
Petalonyx thurberi is a species of flowering plant in the family Loasaceae known by the common names Thurber 's sandpaper plant and common sandpaper plant .
Setchellanthus caeruleus is a species of pungent shrub with large blue flowers .
Notropis telescopus ( telescope shiner ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Notropis .
Arundineae is a tribe of grasses , containing three genera .
Linyphia triangularis is a European species of spider in the family Linyphiidae .
Allomerus is a Neotropical genus of small ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Ceanothus leucodermis , with the common name chaparral whitethorn or chaparral white thorn , is a species of shrub in the buckthorn family Rhamnaceae .
The Sphecidae are a cosmopolitan family of parasitoidal wasps that includes sand wasps , mud daubers , and other thread - waisted wasps .
Nolletia is a genus of flowering plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Sphecomyrma is an extinct genus of ant which inhabited the northern hemisphere of the supercontinent Laurasia approximately 80 mya in the Cretaceous .
Simochromis margaretae is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it is only known from the area of Kigoma in Tanzania .
Baurusuchus is an extinct genus of baurusuchid mesoeucrocodylian from the Late Cretaceous of Brazil .
Agrostis vinealis ( Chinese : 芒剪股颖 ; pinyin : mang jian gu ying ) is a species of grass known by the common names brown bentgrass and brown bent , which can be found from Russia to Mongolia , into China and even Pakistan , and India .
Rissoina bruguieri , common name Bruguiere 's risso , is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Rissoinidae .
Aphaenogaster longaeva is an extinct species of ant in formicid subfamily Myrmicinae known from a solitary Eocene or Oligocene fossil found in North America .
Several species now included in Heterotheca were previously classified in the genus Chrysopsis Heterotheca species are often used as food plants by the larvae of some Lepidoptera species including Schinia lynx , Schinia nubila and Schinia saturata ( all of which have been recorded on Heterotheca subaxillaris ) .
Vanda coerulescens is a species of orchid found from Arunachal Pradesh to China ( southern Yunnan ) .
Erigeron bloomeri is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common name scabland fleabane .
Bathykorus bouilloni is a species of jellyfish first described in 2010 .
Zizaniopsis is a genus of plants in the grass family , native to North and South America .
Siphonostomatoida is an order of copepods , containing around 75 % of all the copepods that parasitise fishes .
Typhlops trinitatus , commonly known as the Trinidad worm snake or Trinidad burrowing snake , is a harmless blind snake species endemic to Trinidad and Tobago .
Proxiuber australis is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Naticidae , the moon snails or necklace shells .
Encelia resinifera , the sticky brittlebush , is a North American species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Incurvarioidea is a superfamily of primitive monotrysian moths in the order Lepidoptera which consists of Leafcutters , yucca moths and relatives .
Asplenium schizotrichum is a species of spleenwort that is endemic to the island of Rarotonga in the Cook Islands .
Clupeonella muhlisi is a species of clupeid fish endemic to Lake Apolyont in Turkey , linked to the Sea of Marmara .
Scincinae are a subfamily of six genera and about 48 species of skinks .
Iris palaestina ( or sometimes Iris palestina ) is a species in the genus Iris , it is also in the subgenus of Scorpiris .
The Choreonematoideae are a monogeneric nongeniculate subfamily of Coralline alga .
Euphorbia esula , commonly known as green spurge or leafy spurge , is a species of spurge native to central and southern Europe ( north to England , the Netherlands , and Germany ) , and eastward through most of Asia north of the Himalaya to Korea and eastern Siberia .
Pentalinon is a genus of flowering plants in the dogbane family , Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1845 .
Aglajidae is a family of often colorful , medium - sized , sea slugs , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks .
Paratoxodera borneana , common name Borneo stick mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Brunei that was first identified as a subspecies of P. cornicollis .
Streptomyces abyssalis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from deep sea sediments in the South China Sea on the Xisha Islands in China .
Equus francisci is an extinct species of Equus ( the genus that includes the horse ) which was native to North America .
Exarrhenus egens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Exarrhenus .
Agaricus deserticola , commonly known as the gasteroid agaricus , is a species of fungus in the Agaricaceae family .
Chaetopappa ericoides is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names rose heath and heath - leaved chaetopappa .
The Colombian screech owl ( Megascops colombianus ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Phenacostethus is a genus of priapum fishes found in freshwater and brackish habitats in southeast Asia .
Atopodentatus is an extinct genus of marine reptile , possibly basal sauropterygian , known from the early Middle Triassic ( Pelsonian substage , Anisian stage ) of Luoping County , Yunnan Province , southwestern China .
Tonna allium , common name the costate tun , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tonnidae , the tun shells .
Afroneta is a genus of sheet weavers that was described by Holm in 1968 .
Stiphodon surrufus is a species of goby endemic to the Philippines where it is only known to occur in Lagu Lagu creek on Leyte Island .
Giordania is a malagasy genus of potter wasps .
The many species of Spondylus vary considerably in appearance and range .
Viburnum cinnamomifolium ( common name cinnamon - leaved viburnum ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Adoxaceae , native to western China .
Asplenium polyodon , commonly known as sickle spleenwort , is a species of fern in the family Aspleniaceae .
Bituminaria morisiana is a perennial Mediterranean herb species in the genus Bituminaria .
Hirtodrosophila confusa is a widespread , but rarely common European species of fruit fly from the family Drosophilidae .
Hymenopappus mexicanus , the Mexican woollywhite , is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Musgravea is a genus of rainforest tree from north - eastern Queensland .
Nepenthes rafflesiana ( /nᵻˈpɛnθiːz ræˌfliːziˈɑːnə/ ; after Stamford Raffles ) , or Raffles ' Pitcher - Plant , is a species of tropical pitcher plant .
It contains only one known species , Stachydeoma graveolens , endemic to the State of Florida in the United States .
Sabicea cinerea , the largeflower woodvine , is a species of flowering plant in the Rubiaceae family .
Eryx jaculus , known commonly as the Javelin sand boa , is a species of snake in the Boidae family .
The Rio Pitzara robber frog , Strabomantis helonotus , is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Engraulisoma taeniatum is a species of characiform fish that is found in Argentina , Brazil , Ecuador and Peru .
Margarites groenlandicus , common name the Greenland margarite or wavy top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Margaritidae .
Dendrocalamus is a tropical Asian genus of giant clumping bamboos in the grass family .
Cynariognathus ( meaning puppy jaw)is an extinct genus of middle sized carnivorous therocephalian from the Tapinocephalus Assemblage Zone of South Africa .
Litoria is a genus of Hylidae tree frogs native to Australia , the Bismarck Archipelago , the Solomon Islands , New Guinea , the Lesser Sunda Islands , the Moluccan Islands , and Timor .
Notaeolidia schmekelae is a species of sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Notaeolidiidae .
Diadorina golbachi is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Diadorina .
Phoxinellus is a genus of cyprinid fishes found in the Balkans .
Belonogaster ( belone - `` needle '' , gaster - `` belly '' ) is a large genus of mainly Afrotropical quasisocial wasps , although some species occur in Arabia and two extend as far as India .
Fejervarya limnocharis is a species of frog found widely distributed in South Asia .
Protetragonites is an extinct genus of ammonoid cephalopods belonging to the family Lytoceratidae .
Blakea attenboroughi is a species of plant in the genus Blakea .
Anguilloides is an extinct genus of prehistoric ray - finned fish that lived from the early to middle Eocene .
Piscivoravis is an extinct genus of fish - eating ornithuromorphs known from the Early Cretaceous Jiufotang Formation ( Aptian age ) of western Liaoning Province , northeastern China .
Calochortus nitidus ( broadfruit mariposa lily ) is a North American species of flowering plants in the lily family native to the northwestern United States .
Vaccinium ovatum is a North American species of flowering shrub known by the common names evergreen huckleberry , winter huckleberry and California huckleberry .
`` Proornis '' is an extinct genus of basal bird from the Early Cretaceous ( Barremian , 130 - 125 mya ? ) of northernmost North Korea .
Cryptodendrum adhaesivum ( adhesive , pizza or nap - edged anemone ) is a species of sea anemone in the family Thalassianthidae .
Stropharia caerulea , commonly known as the blue roundhead , is an inedible species of agaric fungus in the family Strophariaceae .
Allium togashii is a plant species endemic to Japan .
Rhodometrini is a tribe of the geometer moth family ( Geometridae ) , with about 16 species in 2 genera and 1 genus with 1 species tentatively associated with the tribe .
Boonea impressa , common name the impressed odostome , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Synodus orientalis is a species of lizardfish that lives mainly in the Northwest Pacific Ocean .
Lithospermum erythrorhizon , the purple gromwell , red - root gromwell , 紫草 zicao ( Pinyin : zǐcǎo ) , 紫草 murasaki･sō ( Japanese ) is a plant species in the genus Lithospermum .
The only species is Andeabatis chilensis of southern South America .
Austromerope is a genus of forcepfly which contains only two known species , Austromerope poultoni from Western Australia , and the South American Austromerope brasiliensis .
The American flamingo ( Phoenicopterus ruber ) is a large species of flamingo closely related to the greater flamingo and Chilean flamingo .
Euricania facialis is a species of insect in the family Ricaniidae .
Peniocereus is a genus of vining cacti , comprising about 18 species , found from the southwestern United States and Mexico .
Neolebias is a genus of distichodontid fishes found in Africa , with 11 currently recognized species :
The family contains the single genus Carbomyces , which in turn contains three species distributed in the USA and Mexico .
In 2016 , the type species Notocolossus gonzalezparejasi was named and described by Bernardo J. González Riga , Matthew Carl Lamanna , Leonardo Daniel Ortiz David , Jorge Orlando Calvo and Juan P. Coria .
Conus poormani , common name the Poorman 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Awalycaeus is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Alycaeidae .
The Amur leopard ( Panthera pardus orientalis ) is a leopard subspecies native to the Primorye region of southeastern Russia and the Jilin Province of northeast China .
Isolepis inundata is a species of sedge native to Papua New Guinea , Australia and New Zealand .
Rosa hemisphaerica , also known as the sulphur rose , is a rose species with pale yellow flowers native to western Asia .
Rousettus is a genus of Old World fruit bats or megabats .
Hyopsodontidae is an extinct family of unspecialized , primitive mammals from the order Condylarthra , living from the Paleocene to the Eocene in North America and Eurasia .
Lithonida is an order of calcareous sponges in the class Calcarea in the animal phylum Porifera .
Bradypterus is a genus of small insectivorous songbirds ( `` warblers '' ) in the newly recognized grass warbler family ( Locustellidae ) .
Syzygium oleosum , commonly known as the Blue Lilly Pilly , is a species of Syzygium tree native to eastern Australian rainforests and wet sclerophyll forests .
Darlingia is a small genus of two species of rainforest tree from Northern Queensland .
Copeina is a genus of fishes found in the Amazon basin .
Waitea circinata is a species of fungus in the family Corticiaceae .
Parietaria pensylvanica is a species of flowering plant in the nettle family known by the common name Pennsylvania pellitory .
Leptasterias aequalis , common names little six - rayed seastar or six - armed star , is a species of starfish .
Juglans neotropica is a species of plant in the Juglandaceae family .
The African warblers are a newly erected family Macrosphenidae , of songbirds .
Acropora cophodactyla is a species of acroporid coral found in the central Indo - Pacific , Australia , southeast Asia , the Solomon Islands and the western Pacific Ocean .
Cychrus turnai is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that is endemic to Sichuan province of China .
The genus Phaeoclavulina comprises approximately 42 species of coral fungi .
Pseudoxanthomonas japonensis is a species of mesophilic , motile , strictly aerobic , Gram - negative , non - spore - forming , rod - shaped bacteria with one polar flagellum , first isolated from human urine , riverside urban soil and anaerobic digester .
Strobilomyces is a genus of boletes ( mushrooms having a spongy mass of pores under the cap ) .

Castilleja cinerea is a species of Indian paintbrush known by the common name ashgray Indian paintbrush .

Steneromene is a grass moth genus ( family Crambidae ) of subfamily Crambinae , tribe Diptychophorini .

Ehrendorferia ( eardrops ) is a genus of two species of biennial and perennial herbaceous plants native to wildfire - prone areas of California and the Baja California peninsula .
Armorloricus is a genus of nanaloricate loriciferan , small to microscopic marine sediment - dwelling animals .
Ophiomyia is genus of Diptera ( fly ) in the family of Agromyzidae .
Doratodon is an extinct genus of crocodylomorph that was once believed to be a dinosaur .

It is represented by a single species , Rhondes neocaledonicus .

Serapias perez - chiscanoi is a species of orchid endemic to western Portugal and western Spain .
Hara filamentosa is a species of South Asian river catfish endemic to Myanmar where it can be found in the Irrawaddy , Sittang , Salween and Rangoon River drainages .
Callopteus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the Kimmeridgian stage of the Late Jurassic epoch .
Dendrocoelopsis is a genus of freshwater triclad .
Handeliodendron consists of a single species of deciduous tree / shrub native to China , and is classified as rare .

Scotinotylus patellatus is a spider in the species of Linyphiidae or `` sheet weaver '' found in Canada and Alaska , United States .
Turbo lajonkairii , common name the Lajonkairi 's turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Alaemon is a genus of birds in the Alaudidae family .
Tylerichthys is an extinct genus of prehistoric surgeonfish that lived in a coral reef during the Lutetian epoch of what is now Monte Bolca , Italy .
Shorea argentifolia ( also called Dark Red Meranti ) is an emergent rainforest tree species in the Dipterocarpaceae family .
Charonia maculosum is a `` taxon inquirenda '' , a species of doubtful identity .
Cordaicarpus is a form genus named by Geinitz ( 1862 ) , but was redefined by Seward ( 1917 ) to avoid confusion with another genus , and establishing that the genus refers only seeds .
Centaurea jacea ( brown knapweed or brownray knapweed ) is a species of herbaceous perennial plants in the genus Centaurea native to dry meadows and open woodland throughout Europe .
The Carnobacteriaceae are a family of Gram - positive lactic acid bacteria .
Sophineta is an extinct genus of small basal lepidosauromorph reptile known from the Early Triassic ( late Olenekian age ) of Małopolska Province , southern Poland .
Anabarites is a problematic lower Cambrian genus , and is one of the small shelly fossils .
Rhinogobius carpenteri is a freshwater species of goby endemic to the Philippines .
Nicothoe tumulosa is a species of copepod parasitic on the gills of the glypheoid lobster Neoglyphea inopinata .
Annandale 's rat ( Rattus annandalei ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .

Neoregelia cyanea is a plant species in the genus Neoregelia .
The Shanxi sika deer ( Cervus nippon grassianus ) is a possibly extinct subspecies of the sika deer .
Syncope hudsoni ( common name : Hudson 's humming frog ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
The Pacific screech owl ( Megascops cooperi ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .

Pterygoplichthys or commonly known as Janitor fish is a genus of South American armored catfishes .

Sparganium emersum is a species of flowering plant in the cat - tail family known by the common names European bur - reed and unbranched bur - reed .
Dragonets are small , perciform , marine fish of the diverse family Callionymidae ( from the Greek kallis , `` beautiful '' and onyma , `` name '' ) found mainly in the tropical waters of the western Indo - Pacific .
Gastrocopta contracta , common name the bottleneck snaggletooth , is a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vertiginidae , the whorl snails .

Polymorphus is a genus of parasitic worms from the phylum Acanthocephala .

Calydiscoides euzeti Justine , 2007 is a species of monogenean of the family Diplectanidae Monticelli , 1903 .
Diamella cupreomicans is a species of ground beetle in the Lebiinae subfamily that can be found in China , Indonesia , Myanmar , Laos , Malaysia , and Viet Nam .
Dryadissector ( meaning `` Dryad dissector '' in Greek ) is an extinct genus of varanoid lizard represented by the type species Dryadissector shilleri from the Late Cretaceous of Texas .
Tachina vernalis is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to Europe , but was introduced to New England .
Schiedea sarmentosa is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name cliff schiedea .
Diabolepis ( or Diabolichthys ) is an extinct genus of very primitive lungfish which lived about 400 million years ago , in the Early Devonian period of South China .
Psidium sintenisii is a species of flowering plant in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae .
Hippoboscoidea is the name of a superfamily of the Calyptratae .
Lobatus raninus , common name the hawk - wing conch , is a species of medium to large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
The Unscented Dendrobium ( Dendrobium anosmum ) is a species of epiphytic orchid .
Calabazo virus is an enveloped , single - stranded , negative - sense RNA hantavirus species of the Bunyaviridae family .
Barbus fasciolatus , the African banded barb , Angola barb , blue - barred barb or fire barb is a ray - finned fish species in the family Cyprinidae .
Taeniopsetta is a genus of small lefteye flounders native to the Indo - Pacific at depths of 150 to 300 m ( 490 to 980 ft ) .
Schistosoma mansoni infects about 83.31 million people worldwide , causing the disease intestinal schistosomiasis ( schistosomiasis caused by all the Schistosoma species infects over 200 million people . )
Blachia umbellata is a species of plants under the family Euphorbiaceae .
Crepipatella dilatata is a species of sea snail described by Lamarck .
Rhizanthella , commonly known as underground orchids , is a small epiparasitic , achlorophyllous , subterranean genus of orchid .
Japanese seabream , Pagrus major , is a fish species in the Sparidae family .
Astragalus lentiginosus is a species of legume known by the common names spotted locoweed and freckled milkvetch .
Speirantha is a genus of one known species of flowering plants found in south - east China .
Habranthus ( copperlily ) is a genus of tender herbaceous flowering bulbs in the Amaryllidaceae family , subfamily Amaryllidoideae .
Originally the heliozoa were treated together as a formal taxon Heliozoa or Heliozoea , with the rank of class or phylum , but it has been realised that they are polyphyletic , as the various orders show notable differences and are no longer believed to be descended from a single common ancestor .
Propantodice grisea is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Propantodice .
Uroptychus anacaena is a species of chirostylid squat lobster first found in Taiwan .
Cytinus hypocistis is an ant - pollinated species of parasitic plant in the family Cytinaceae having four subspecies .
The Five - lined Mabuya ( Trachylepis quinquetaeniata , formerly Mabuya quinquetaeniata ) , sometimes called Rainbow Mabuya , blue - tailed Skink ( due to the blue tail ) or Rainbow Skink is a species of African skink in the subfamily Lygosominae .
Aphanopetalum clematideum is a species of twining shrub or vines that grows in the Geraldton Sandplains region of Western Australia .
Cataclysta lampetialis is a Crambidae species in the genus Cataclysta .
The Príncipe speirops ( Zosterops leucophoeus ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Macaranga quadricornis is a species of plant in the family Euphorbiaceae .
Pterocaulon is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family , native to North and South America and to Australasia .
Aulotrachichthys is a genus of slimeheads .
Phyllopetalia excrescens is a species of dragonfly in the family Austropetaliidae .
Gaylussacia orocola , the Blue Ridge huckleberry , is a plant species native to the coastal plains of the southeastern United States ( Louisiana , Mississippi , Alabama , Georgia , Florida ) .
Stagmomantis amazonica , common name Amazon mantis , is a species of praying mantis in the genus Stagmomantis .
Mccoskerichthys sandae , the Tufted blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny , found around Costa Rica and Panama , in the eastern central Pacific ocean .
Thesprotia insolita , common name Costa Rican grass mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Costa Rica .
Calvatia bovista is a species of Calvatia mushroom , the second largest Calvatia in North America .
Procephalaspis is an extinct genus of jawless fish .
Hohenbergia stellata is a perennial species of the genus Hohenbergia .
Schizoglossa major was a species of large predatory , air - breathing , land slug , a carnivorous terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Rhytididae .
Litoporus dimona is a cellar spider species found in Brazil .
Atractaspis aterrima , commonly known as the slender burrowing asp or mole viper , is a species of venomous snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Pirulintia angelinae is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pirulintia .
Apophysomyces variabilis is one of four species in the genus Apophysomyces , which also includes A. elegans , A. ossiformis , and A. trapeziformis .
Cystoderma carcharias , is a species of agaric in the fungal family Agaricaceae .
Dihammaphoroides sanguinicollis ' is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae .
Brochuchus is an extinct genus of crocodile known from the Miocene Hiwegi Formation of Rusinga Island in Lake Victoria , Kenya .
Coryphaenoides rupestris is a species of marine ray - finned fish in the family Macrouridae .
Protonyctia originalis is a moth in the Douglasiidae family , and the only species in the genus Protonyctia .
Draba sierrae is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Sierra draba .
It consists of only one species , Semicalamidia owgarra , which was described by Rothschild in 1912 .
Penicillium ornatum is an anamorph , species of the genus of Penicillium .
Mystus vittatus , the striped dwarf catfish , is a species of catfish of the family Bagridae .
Axiologina ferumequinum is a species of ulidiidae or picture - winged fly in the genus Axiologina of the family Ulidiidae .
Miscanthus sinensis is a species of flowering plant in the grass family Poaceae , native to eastern Asia throughout most of China , Japan , Taiwan and Korea .
Philiris fulgens , commonly known as the Purple Moonbeam , is a species of butterfly of the Lycaenidae family .
Harttia kronei is a species of armored catfish of the family endemic to Brazil where it is found in the Ribeira de Iguape River basin .
Coptosapelteae is a tribe incertae sedis of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family and contains about 55 species in 2 genera .
Haliotis roei , common name Roe 's abalone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Sauropus assimilis is an extremely rare species of plant in the Phyllanthaceae family .
Callopistes is a lizard genus which belongs to the family of Teiidae .
Eburia cinerea is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family that is endemic to Peru .
Leymus akmolinensis is a species of grass endemic to Russia and Kazakhstan .
Aipysurus duboisii , also known as the Dubois ' sea snake or reef shallows sea snake , is a species of venomous sea snake .
Palaeomastodon an extinct genus of Proboscidea .
Penicillium pseudostromaticum is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from the mushroom Piptoporus betulinus which grew on the tree Betula populifolia .
Apoanagyrus lopezi is a species of parasitic wasp native to Central America .
The Differently Colored Catasetum ( Catasetum discolor ) is a species of orchid .
Carphochaete bigelovii , common name Bigelow 's bristlehead , is a species of North American flowering plants in the sunflower family .
It is endemic to Australia and contains only one species , Actites megalocarpa commonly known as the Dune Thistle , Beach Thistle or Coastal Sow Thistle .

Hylarana margariana ( Irrawaddy frog ) is a species of true frog in the genus Hylarana .

Erginus rubellus is a species of sea snail , a true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Acmaeidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Parthenocissus henryana ( Chinese Virginia - creeper or silver vein creeper ) is a species of flowering plant in the vine family Vitaceae , native to China .

Iris reticulata ( netted iris ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Iridaceae .
Leptotes vellozicola is a species of orchid endemic to Brazil ( Bahia ) .
Lagenandra dewitii is a plant species belonging to the aroid genus Lagenandra .

Grevillea monslacana , commonly known as Lake Mountain Grevillea , is a shrub species which is endemic to mountainous areas of eastern Victoria in Australia .
Parcoblatta virginica , the Virginia wood cockroach , is a small cockroach species of the genus Parcoblatta , measuring about a centimeter long as an adult .
Cotyachryson philippii is a species of round - necked longhorns beetle belonging to the family Cerambycidae , subfamily Cerambycinae .
Beroe ovata is a pelagic species and has a wide distribution in the Atlantic Ocean and Mediterranean Sea .

In taxonomy , the Halobacteriales are an order of the Halobacteria , found in water saturated or nearly saturated with salt .

Megabunus diadema is a species of harvestman widely distributed in Europe , where it has been found in Iceland , Faroe Islands , Western Norway , Great Britain , Western France , Belgium and Northern Spain .

Micrurus bernadi is a species of venomous elapid snake , endemic to eastern Mexico .

Pectis cylindrica ( Sonoran cinchweed ) is an annual plant and species of Pectis .
The South African shelduck or Cape shelduck ( Tadorna cana ) is a species of shelduck , a group of large goose - like birds which are part of the bird family Anatidae , which also includes the swans , geese and ducks .
Cerianthus lloydii is a species of tube - dwelling sea anemone in the family Cerianthidae .
The Caudovirales are an order of viruses also known as the tailed bacteriophages .
Nesocordulia villiersi is a species of dragonfly in family Corduliidae .
Liotiidae is a family of small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Vetigastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Rubus liebmannii is a Mesoamerican species of brambles in the rose family .

Nycteroleteridae is a family of procolophonian parareptilians ( early extinct reptiles ) from the Middle to Late Permian of Russia and North America .
Neoclinus bryope , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around Japan and South Korea in the western Pacific ocean , and around California in the eastern Pacific .
Veronica peregrina is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by several common names including neckweed , American speedwell , purslane speedwell and hairy purslane speedwell .
Mysidae is the largest family of crustaceans in the order Mysida , with over 1000 species in around 170 genera .

Gamochaeta stagnalis , the Desert cudweed , is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .

Aetheliparis is a genus of snailfishes with one species known from the Atlantic Ocean off the coast of North America and the other from the Pacific Ocean near New Zealand .

It was described in 2011 , and is the only species in the genus Taebaeksaukia .

Hadrosauroidea is a clade or superfamily of ornithischian dinosaurs that includes the `` duck - billed '' dinosaurs , or hadrosaurids , and all dinosaurs more closely related to them than to Iguanodon .
