Multidentula ovularis is a species of minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Enidae .
Belemnitella is a genus of belemnite from the Late Cretaceous of Europe and North America .
Box kite spiders is a common name for the Afrotropical Isoxya genus of orb - weaver spiders .
Octamyrtus is a group of plantss in the myrtle family Myrtaceae described as a genus in 1922 .
Seyrigia albopunctata is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Seyrigia .
Quercus infectoria ( Aleppo oak ) is a species of oak , bearing galls that have been traditionally used for centuries in Asia medicinally .
Chikku Chikku ( Hypochaeris sessiliflora ) is a South American species of plants in the daisy family .
Allium chrysocephalum is a plant species native to China , in the provinces Gansu , Qinghai , and Sichuan .
The Sierolomorphidae are a family of about 10 known species of wasps , all in the genus Sierolomorpha , found in the Northern Hemisphere .
Euphorbia resinifera ( Resin spurge ) is a species of spurge native to Morocco , where it occurs on the slopes of the Atlas Mountains .
Ancylostoma pluridentatum is a species of parasitic hookworm that infects wild species of cats .
Divarilima pellucida is a species of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Limidae .
Anyphaenidae is a family araneomorph spiders , sometimes called anyphaenid sac spiders .
Delonix baccal is a species of leguminous tree in the Fabaceae family .
Aparescus praecox is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Aparescus .
The Yunnan lake newt ( Cynops wolterstorffi ) is a species of newt in the Salamandridae family , and is also known as Wolterstorff 's newt .
Amietophrynus reesi , the Merara toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Dyspanopeus sayi is a species of mud crab that is native to the Atlantic coast of North America .
Blister beetles are beetles of the family Meloidae , so called for their defensive secretion of a blistering agent , cantharidin .
Balistoides is a genus of triggerfishes native to the Indo - Pacific region .
Nembrotha lineolata is a species of nudibranch , a sea slug , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Polyceridae .
Papaver pygmaeum is a species of poppy known by the common name alpine glacier poppy .
Minuartia rosei is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names peanut sandwort and peanut stitchwort .
Prototocyon or Sivacyon is an extinct genus of small omnivorous canid living during the Pleistocene .
Scarabaeus sacer is a species of dung beetle belonging to the family Scarabaeidae .
Paphiopedilum druryi is a species of orchid endemic to the Travancore Hills of southern India .
Fritillaria fusca is an Asian species of herbaceous plant in the lily family , native to Tibet .
Nebria dejeanii is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Austria .
Allium runyonii is a North American species of wild onion native to southern Texas about as far north as Corpus Christi , as well as to the Mexican States of Nuevo León and Tamaulipas .
Packera cardamine is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name bittercress ragwort .
Tridysderina is a genus of goblin spider .
Cicindela highlandensis is a species of beetle known by the common name Highlands tiger beetle .
Parasphaerichthys is a genus of gouramies known only from Myanmar .
Geastrum pectinatum is an inedible species of mushroom belonging to the earthstar family of fungi .
Agaricus hondensis , commonly known as the felt - ringed agaricus , is a species of fungus in the family Agaricaceae .
Conus magnificus , common name the `` magnificent cone '' , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
The Pteranodontidae are a family of large pterosaurs of the Cretaceous Period of North America .
Craterocephalus marjoriae , commonly known as Marjorie 's hardyhead or silverstreak hardyhead , is a species of fish in the family Atherinidae that is native to eastern Australia , namely central Queensland to northeastern New South Wales .
Musca osiris is a species of fly in the genus Musca .
Cleisostoma is a genus of orchid with approximately 90 accepted species widely distributed through much of the Indian Subcontinent , Southeast Asia , China , New Guinea , and some of the islands of the Western Pacific .
Chelon is a genus of mullets found in coastal marine waters , estuaries and rivers in the Indo - Pacific and northeast Atlantic , including the Mediterranean .
Althaspis is an extinct genus of pteraspidid heterostracan agnathan .
Millotia is a genus of small annual herbs in the pussy's - toes tribe within the sunflower family .
Sarocalamus is a genus of Asian bamboo in the grass family .
Liatris helleri is a species of flowering plants in the aster family known by the common names Heller 's blazing star and Heller 's gayfeather .
Danocrania is an extinct genus of brachiopod from the Upper Cretaceous and Lower Paleocene of Europe and Australia .
Sattar snowtrout ( Schizothorax curvifrons ) is a species of cyprinid native to southern Asia from Iran to China where it can be found in most types of freshwater habitats .
Harpathaumas priscus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Harpathaumas .
Acer stewarti is an extinct maple species in the family Sapindaceae described from a series of fossil leaves and samaras .
The genus is monotypic and contains the single species Xyleborus sporodochifer , first reported in 2007 , and found in the Ozarks in Missouri .
Hierochloe occidentalis is a species of grass known by the common name California sweetgrass .
Merlucciidae are a family of cod - like fish , including most hakes .
It consists of only one species , Pelzia alticolana , which is found in Ecuador ( Carchi Province ) .
Amanita sphaerobulbosa , commonly known as the Asian abrupt - bulbed Lepidella , is a species of agaric fungus in the family Amanitaceae .
Osteopilus is a genus of frogs in the Hylidae family .
Anthracobune ( `` coal mound '' ) is an extinct genus of stem perissodactyl from the middle Eocene of the Upper Kuldana Formation of Kohat , Punjab , Pakistan .
Dendrobium unicum is a species of orchid , commonly known as the Unique Dendrobium native to Indochina ( Thailand , Laos , Vietnam ) .
Cleithrolepis is an extinct genus of ray - finned fish from the Triassic .
Eliotia is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . It is a synonym of Rachana since Eliotia is preoccupied
Limnophora is a genus of flies , belonging to the family Muscidae .
Austrostipa crinita is a species of grass that grows in coastal parts of midwest Western Australia .
Muraenosaurus ( from the Latin `` Muraena '' meaning `` eel '' and `` Sauros '' meaning lizard ) is an extinct genus of cryptoclidid plesiosaur reptile from the Oxford Clay of Southern England .
Scabroschema scabricolle is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Scabroschema .
Mordacia lapicida , also known as the Chilean Lamprey , is a species of southern topeyed lamprey endemic to southern Chile , where it can be found in riverine and marine habitats .
Sathrophyllia is a genus of Asian katydid .
Thomas 's fruit - eating bat ( Artibeus watsoni ) , sometimes also popularly called Watson 's fruit - eating bat , is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .
Arctosa fulvolineata is a wolf spider species in the genus Arctosa found in Europe , Mallorca and North Africa .
Hemiphruda mecasa is a moth in the Drepanidae family and only species in the Hemiphruda genus .
Zodarion styliferum is a spider species found in Portugal , Spain and Madeira .
Epimecis scolopaiae is a species of moth in the family Geometridae , subfamily Ennominae .
Reichardia ligulata is a species of plants in the dandelion tribe within the daisy family ( Asteraceae ) native to the Canary Islands ( Tenerife , Grand Canaria and La Palma ) where it grows within gravel piles upon coastal cliffs .
Sarcodon imbricatus , commonly known as the shingled hedgehog or scaly hedgehog , is a species of tooth fungus in the order Thelephorales .
Sclerorhynchus is an extinct genus of primitive batoidean that lived in the Cretaceous .
Megachile fidelis , the faithful leafcutting bee , is a species of bee in the Megachile genus .
Turbo crassus , common name the crass turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Adonidia is a genus of flowering plants in the Arecaceae family .
Rodriguezia candida is a species of orchid native to Venezuela , Brazil , French Guiana , Suriname .
Vendia is a genus of oval - shaped , Ediacaran fossils ranging from 4.5 to 12.5 mm long .
The Solanaceae , or nightshades , are an economically important family of flowering plants .
Megacephala wimmeri is a brown coloured species of ground beetle in the subfamily of Carabinae that was described by Mandl in 1958 , and is endemic to Santa Cruz , Bolivia .
Mentzelia densa is a species of flowering plant in the Loasaceae known by the common names Royal Gorge blazingstar and Royal Gorge stickleaf .
Alsodes pehuenche ( common name : Pehuenche spiny - chest frog ) is a species of frog in the Alsodidae family .
Rhynocoris iracundus is a species of assassin and thread - legged bugs belonging to the family Reduviidae , subfamily Harpactorinae .
Eleutherodactylus aporostegus ( commonly known as the Tiburon burrowing frog ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family .
Praealticus natalis , the Natal blenny or the Natal rockskipper , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific and Indian ocean .
Paysonia auriculata , the Earleaf bladderpod , is a plant species native to the south - central part of the United States .
Lentinula lateritia is a species of agaric fungus in the family Omphalotaceae .
Biebersteinia is a genus containing four species of herbs in the flowering plant order Sapindales .
Pholidichthys is a genus of perciform fish which consists of two species of the tropical Pacific Ocean .
Erronea onyx , common name the onyx cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Atractaspis congica , or the Congo burrowing asp , is a species of venomous snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Astarte castanea , or the chestnut astarte , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Astartidae .
Sociala is an extinct genus of cockroach which existed in what is now France during the early Cretaceous period ( Albian age ) .
Bombus ignitus is a species of bumblebee in the family Apidae .
Leptocharacidium omospilus is a species of fish in the Crenuchidae family ( South American darters ) .
Eulogia is a genus of the moth of the Pyralidae family containing only one species , the Broad - banded Eulogia Moth , Eulogia ochrifrontella .
Aphonopelma armada is a species of spider in the family Theraphosidae , found in United States ( Texas ) .
Machairodus is a genus of large machairodontine saber - toothed cats that lived in Europe , Asia , Africa and North America during the late Miocene .
Harpalus punctipennis is a species of ground beetle from Harpalinae subfamily that can be found in French and Italian Alps .
Psaltoda moerens , commonly known as the redeye , is an Australian species of cicada .
Carabus alexandrae cratocephaloides is a subspecies of black coloured beetle from Carabidae family that is endemic to Gansu , China .
The Diprionidae are a small family of conifer - feeding sawflies ( thus the common name conifer sawflies , though other Symphyta feed on conifers ) restricted to the Northern Hemisphere , with some 90 species in 11 genera worldwide .
Cypripedium yatabeanum , common name spotted lady slipper , is a species of terrestrial orchids .
In taxonomy , Ignisphaera is a genus of the Desulfurococcales .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Pseudoparodia pseudopeziza .
Eutudora jimenoi is a species of an operculate land snail , terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Pomatiidae .
Melanoxanthus yushiroi is a species of beetle from the Elateridae family .
Calumma boettgeri , commonly known as Boettger 's chameleon or the blue - nosed chameleon , is a chameleon species endemic to northern Madagascar , and common in the forests of Nosy Be .
Penstemon grinnellii is a species of penstemon known by the common name Grinnell 's beardtongue .
Euphorbia paralias ( sea spurge ) is a species of Euphorbia , native to Europe , northern Africa , and western Asia .
Oryzias curvinotus or the Malabar ricefish are a freshwater -- brackish fish species native to the Gulf of Kutch to Trivandrum , Kerala , India .
Terebratula is a modern genus of brachiopod with a fossil record dating back to the Late Devonian .
Gagata youssoufi is a species of sisorid catfish native to India and Bangladesh .
Callionymus aagilis , the Slow dragonet , is a species of dragonet native to the Indian Ocean around Réunion and Mauritius .
Struthiocephalus ( `` Ostrich Head '' ) is an extinct genus of dinocephalian therapsid from the Permian of South Africa .
Barry McDaniel ( born October 18 , 1930 in Lyndon , Kansas ) is an American operatic baritone who spent his career almost exclusively in Germany .
Eleanor Lausch Dietrich ( Brooklyn , NY , July 30 , 1912 - Island Park , NY , May 4 , 2001 ) was an American operatic soprano .
Andrzej Dobber ( born May 28 , 1961 in Więcbork , Poland ) is an operatic baritone .
Patrizia Ciofi ( born 7 June 1967 ) is an Italian operatic Coloratura soprano .
Jacques Isnardon ( 15 February 1860 - 14 November 1930 ) was a French bass - baritone , writer and voice teacher .
Marina Prior ( born 18 October 1963 ) is an Australian soprano and actress with a career mainly in musical theatre .
Harriett Abrams ( born c. 1758- died 8 March 1821 , Torquay ) was an English soprano and composer .
Libuše Domanínská ( surname also Klobásková and Vyčichlováborn ; 4 July 1924 , Brno ) is a Czech classical soprano who had an active career in concerts and operas from the 1940s through the 1970s .
Allan James Foley ( Signor Foli ) ( 7 August 1837 -- 10 October 1899 ) , distinguished 19th century Irish bass opera singer , was born at Cahir , Tipperary .
Philip Ritte ( 8 January 1871 -- 14 December 1954 ) was a British tenor of the early 20th century .
